Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.58,0:00:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to JW Broadcasting! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.92,0:00:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s what we \Ncan look forward to in our program: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.19,0:00:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What if your courtship \Nreveals problems you didn’t expect? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.60,0:00:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Part 3 of the Preparing for Marriage series \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.17,0:00:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,will show us how we \Ncan “calculate the expense” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.14,0:00:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,when considering marriage. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.54,0:00:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We go to Australia \Nto meet Viv and Ann Mouritz. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.98,0:00:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Their life of full-time service \Nhas taken them around the world. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.45,0:00:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What advice do they have \Nfor those who are deciding \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.32,0:00:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,what form \Nof sacred service to pursue? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.49,0:00:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ll enjoy \Na music video that highlights \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.89,0:00:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the theme of our program. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.89,0:00:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It will encourage us to settle differences \Nwith our brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.99,0:00:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and to forgive one another. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.50,0:00:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the October 2016 edition \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.20,0:00:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of JW Broadcasting!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.36,0:01:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin with a report from Ukraine. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.33,0:01:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In 2014, \Npolitical tensions in eastern Ukraine \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.40,0:01:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,boiled over \Ninto a full-blown military conflict. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.33,0:01:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Within months, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.34,0:01:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,over 7,600 Witnesses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.24,0:01:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,needed to flee the area \Nto seek refuge. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.97,0:01:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Others sheltered in their homes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.71,0:01:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,How did our brothers \Nsurvive physically \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.11,0:01:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and spiritually \Nthrough the fighting? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.48,0:01:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Relief was organized \Nfrom hundreds of miles away \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.75,0:01:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,at the branch office in L’viv. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.29,0:01:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following interviews, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.59,0:01:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,our brothers and sisters \Ndescribe the love and care \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.96,0:01:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they received from the organization \Nand from each other.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.55,0:02:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It happened that the hostilities \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.82,0:02:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,started without warning, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.95,0:02:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the brothers needed to flee quickly.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.22,0:02:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There was not enough food; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.22,0:02:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,there was nothing in the stores; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.36,0:02:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,there was a lack of medicine; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.36,0:02:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,there was no water, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.36,0:02:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,no electricity.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.93,0:02:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It was scary. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.77,0:02:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no stability at all. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.60,0:02:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We did not know what to do.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.67,0:02:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we stay, or should we leave?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.78,0:02:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There were triplets; \Nthey were seven years old. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.25,0:02:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as they \Ngot into the shelter, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.38,0:02:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they started singing \Na Kingdom song. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.02,0:02:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The adults \Nalso joined them in singing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.29,0:02:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and because of that, \Nwe couldn’t hear the explosions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.16,0:03:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that were happening outside.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.10,0:03:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,True, we ran out of foodstuffs, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.63,0:03:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and we had no money. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.70,0:03:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But I knew we would be able to get by. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.71,0:03:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,God would not let us die of hunger.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.64,0:03:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the shelling was happening\Nso often, it was impossible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.85,0:03:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to conduct our usual meetings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.85,0:03:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We also couldn’t organize the ministry \Nin the normal way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.05,0:03:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just too dangerous.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.79,0:03:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,When we received the first reports \Nabout the unrest in the east, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.19,0:03:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,our Branch Committee gathered \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.19,0:03:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and we prayerfully analyzed \Nthe situation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.13,0:03:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We asked Jehovah for wisdom\N—how to act, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.53,0:03:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,how to help our brothers \Nto be spiritually and physically safe. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.24,0:03:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We were also sending regular\Nupdate reports to the Governing Body.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.77,0:03:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,More than 156 tons of food \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.91,0:03:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and 21 tons of clothing donated \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.05,0:03:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,by local brothers have been distributed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.55,0:03:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to fellow believers \Nand also to some non-Witnesses.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.79,0:03:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We had been told \Nthat we would be receiving \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.82,0:04:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,about five tons of relief supplies. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.82,0:04:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So we were astounded \Nwhen instead of 5 tons, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.33,0:04:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we received 15 tons!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.33,0:04:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It was lovely to find little notes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.80,0:04:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that our brothers \Nand sisters had written \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.37,0:04:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and included in the packages.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.11,0:04:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers from neighboring cities responded \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.94,0:04:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and offered their homes, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.11,0:04:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,provided foodstuffs \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.11,0:04:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and, more importantly, \Ntheir brotherly hospitality.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.25,0:04:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So we are ready to make sacrifices, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.75,0:04:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to adjust our schedules, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.96,0:04:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and to even take time \Nout from our families \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.82,0:04:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to render practical help \Nto our brothers.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.53,0:04:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,For example,\Nbeginning at 6 a.m., \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.60,0:04:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I would visit \Nthe brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.27,0:04:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and bring them \Nthe things that they needed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.87,0:04:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So during two and a half months of war \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.11,0:04:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and two months of reconstruction, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.18,0:04:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I rode my bicycle \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.18,0:05:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,6,500 kilometers.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.78,0:05:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The local elders from Slavyansk \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.59,0:05:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,organized small congregations \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.79,0:05:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and regularly conducted meetings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.79,0:05:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to support them spiritually.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.96,0:05:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Major repairs \Nhave been carried out on 20 houses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.96,0:05:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of brothers and sisters, \Nand minor repair work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.57,0:05:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,was done on 72 houses \Nand apartments.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.47,0:05:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We prepared two more programs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.64,0:05:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, not only \Nfor the congregations in the war zone \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.24,0:05:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but for the whole country of Ukraine, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.31,0:05:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,even for Russia and Belarus. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.48,0:05:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We even had 325,000 \Nin attendance.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.82,0:05:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,An interesting experience \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.82,0:05:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,was the response of the people \Nwho were not Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.76,0:05:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They belong to another religion, \Nyet they said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.36,0:05:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“You are the only ones \Nthat really care. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.57,0:05:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Your genuine love \Nis shown by your deeds.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.97,0:05:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what makes us different \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.87,0:05:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,from all other religions.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.21,0:06:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This unselfish love \Nshown by our brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.81,0:06:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,did not go unnoticed \Nby my husband and my son. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.82,0:06:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband \Nstarted studying the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.89,0:06:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and he regularly attends \Nthe meetings now. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.62,0:06:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently, he enrolled \Nin the Theocratic Ministry School.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.59,0:06:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I experienced this love personally, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.40,0:06:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and I started studying \Nthe Bible again with the brothers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.77,0:06:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I am preparing for baptism.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.64,0:06:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, \None of our sisters was killed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.44,0:06:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that a person can lose\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.81,0:06:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,—lose everything, but that \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.11,0:06:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is really nothing \Ncompared to losing your children. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.02,0:06:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers and sisters listened to us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.95,0:06:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We cried together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.96,0:06:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I just can’t put it into words. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.73,0:06:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It is as if Jehovah \Nis holding you in his arms\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.93,0:06:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,—he doesn’t let you fall—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.93,0:06:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,as if he is saying to you: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.93,0:06:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Don’t let go, my dear one. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.27,0:07:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m helping you. \NI’m supporting you.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.61,0:07:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,With Jehovah there are no borders \Nbetween nations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.41,0:07:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I could see \Nthat this was the true religion.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.52,0:07:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We continue to pray \Nfor our brothers in Ukraine. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.39,0:07:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re confident \Nof Jehovah’s love for them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.66,0:07:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and we know he’ll sustain them \Nthrough any tribulation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.26,0:07:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Our worldwide brotherhood \Nis truly special. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.80,0:07:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When our brothers are in need, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.00,0:07:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to help \Nin whatever way possible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.67,0:07:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It also brings us great joy \Nto be with our brothers\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.87,0:07:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,—whether at the meetings, \Nin the field service, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.61,0:07:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,or on other occasions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.61,0:07:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We love our brothers \Nand enjoy spending time with them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.28,0:07:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, \Nbecause we are all imperfect, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.69,0:07:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,our love and unity will be tested. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.69,0:07:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We may have our feelings hurt, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.96,0:07:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or we may hurt\Nthe feelings of others.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.90,0:08:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That brings me to the theme \NI would like to discuss \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.36,0:08:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,with you \Nin this month’s program, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.77,0:08:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Settling Differences \NBrings Jehovah’s Favor.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.57,0:08:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It is based on Matthew 6:14. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.44,0:08:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read \Nthis important verse together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.98,0:08:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Right after teaching \Nhis disciples how to pray, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.31,0:08:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus says in verse 14: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.89,0:08:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“For if you forgive \Nmen their trespasses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.96,0:08:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,your heavenly Father \Nwill also forgive you.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.13,0:08:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,To what extent do Jesus’ words \Naffect how Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.40,0:08:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,views what we do each day \Nin our worship to him? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.93,0:08:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider this: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.93,0:08:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re concluding \Nyour day in prayer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.60,0:08:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You pray for Jehovah’s name \Nto be sanctified. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.14,0:08:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You pray \Nfor his Kingdom to come. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.68,0:08:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You ask that he bless \Nthe Governing Body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.15,0:08:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and the brothers taking the lead. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.28,0:08:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You share with him \Na few matters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.62,0:08:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of personal concern. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.62,0:08:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you say: “Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.62,0:08:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“I know I am imperfect, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.62,0:09:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“and I sin against you often. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.82,0:09:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“Please forgive me \Nfor my sins. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.36,0:09:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let me stand before you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.36,0:09:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in a clean \Nand approved state.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.83,0:09:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the question is, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.84,0:09:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Has Jehovah heard \Nyour heartfelt request? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.91,0:09:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Will he forgive you? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.04,0:09:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what did Jesus say? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.38,0:09:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Look again at verse 14: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.11,0:09:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“For if you forgive \Nmen their trespasses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.45,0:09:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,your heavenly Father \Nwill also forgive you.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.09,0:09:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice \NJesus’ use of the word “if”? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.96,0:09:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That tells us that forgiveness \Nis not automatic. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.56,0:09:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes with a condition, or price. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.03,0:09:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What price? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.70,0:09:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,According to Jesus, \N‘if we forgive others,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.50,0:09:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the condition has been met; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.50,0:09:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the price has been paid. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.91,0:09:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What will Jehovah do for us? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.38,0:09:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said: \N“[He] will also forgive you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.25,0:10:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, though, \Nis it fair or reasonable \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.12,0:10:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,for Jehovah to say to us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.12,0:10:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Only if you forgive others, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.12,0:10:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,then I will also forgive you’? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.32,0:10:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, suppose you \Nget very sick and lose your job. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.26,0:10:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re unable \Nto pay rent for many months. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.60,0:10:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Your situation is desperate. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.07,0:10:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You have very few,\Nif any, options. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.47,0:10:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You worry about your wife \Nand your children. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.07,0:10:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Say you go to the owner \Nof the house and ask \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.28,0:10:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,if he would give you time \Nto get back on your feet. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.45,0:10:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you get better \Nand are able to work again, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.58,0:10:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you will do everything \Nwithin your power \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.65,0:10:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to pay him what you owe.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.06,0:10:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He tells you not to worry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.59,0:10:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He understands your situation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.26,0:10:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He will cancel your debt, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.26,0:10:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and you do not have \Nto pay him any rent \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.53,0:10:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,until your situation improves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.67,0:10:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, he’ll cover \Nyour monthly expenses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.80,0:10:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,until you are able \Nto care for your family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.27,0:11:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How would you feel \Nabout what he has done, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.61,0:11:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and would this affect \Nhow you treat others?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.21,0:11:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, because of our sinful nature, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.78,0:11:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,we are all in debt to Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.05,0:11:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,—deserving of death. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.12,0:11:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We are unable \Nto cover our expenses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.92,0:11:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But when we go \Nto Jehovah in prayer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.49,0:11:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and beg for his help, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.70,0:11:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in his great mercy and kindness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.63,0:11:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,he tells us not to worry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.63,0:11:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He has given the life \Nof his Son to pay our debt. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.04,0:11:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And on the basis of that sacrifice, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.81,0:11:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He is willing to cover our expenses\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.61,0:11:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,—the sins we commit daily—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.71,0:11:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and to extend forgiveness \Nto us until we are able \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.12,0:11:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to get back on our feet, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.12,0:11:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when we reach perfection \Nin the new world.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.52,0:11:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So think again about those \Nsimple yet powerful words \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.39,0:11:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jesus at Matthew 6:14: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.56,0:11:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“For if you forgive \Nmen their trespasses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.03,0:11:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,your heavenly Father \Nwill also forgive you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.17,0:12:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that fair? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.24,0:12:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that reasonable? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.31,0:12:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it realistic? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.31,0:12:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a doubt! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.31,0:12:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, settling differences, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.55,0:12:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,or forgiving others freely, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.58,0:12:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of the best ways to imitate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.92,0:12:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s compassionate \Nand merciful nature.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.02,0:12:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What can help us \Nto settle differences quickly? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.19,0:12:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing \Nwe should do is to try \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.53,0:12:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and let love cover \Nover the wrong. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.00,0:12:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I just forgive and forget? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.30,0:12:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If we are able to do so, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.57,0:12:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,this is a beautiful way to maintain \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.77,0:12:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the congregation’s peace and unity. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.51,0:12:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we’re struggling \Nto forget the wrong, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.24,0:12:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,there are two scriptures \Nthat are especially helpful \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.18,0:12:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in this matter \Nof settling differences. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.78,0:12:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They are Matthew 5:23, 24 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.12,0:12:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and Matthew 18:15-17.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.19,0:12:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep in mind that these texts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.26,0:13:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,are not referring \Nto the same scenarios, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.20,0:13:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,nor are they to be applied \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.20,0:13:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,in the exact same way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.57,0:13:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew chapter 5 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.57,0:13:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,has a broader application \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.71,0:13:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and can be used to bring peace \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.71,0:13:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in most situations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.71,0:13:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew chapter 18 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.91,0:13:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,has a more limited application \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.55,0:13:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and applies to specific situations \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.48,0:13:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that are more serious in nature.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.45,0:13:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s consider the first text, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.59,0:13:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew 5:23, 24: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.93,0:13:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“If, then, \Nyou are bringing your gift to the altar \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.20,0:13:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“and there you remember that \Nyour brother has something against you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.87,0:13:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“leave your gift there \Nin front of the altar, and go away. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.00,0:13:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“First make your peace \Nwith your brother, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.74,0:13:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and then come back \Nand offer your gift.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.98,0:13:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,To truly capture \Nwhat these two brief verses mean \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.25,0:13:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,for you and me today, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.28,0:13:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to understand \Nwhat Jesus’ words meant \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.02,0:13:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to his first-century Jewish listeners. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.32,0:14:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Picture the scene in your mind \Nas we transport ourselves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.79,0:14:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,into the city of Jerusalem \Nsome 2,000 years ago. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.60,0:14:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It is during one \Nof the annual festivals. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.87,0:14:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There are tens of thousands \Nof people in the city. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.40,0:14:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You are there to make your sacrifice\N—a beautiful lamb. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.14,0:14:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The best one you have. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.14,0:14:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s clean and unblemished.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.88,0:14:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You take the lamb \Nthrough a series of courts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.75,0:14:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,all the way \Nto the Court of Priests. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.08,0:14:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It has taken you \Nmost of the day to get there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.09,0:14:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you’re ready \Nto put your hands on that animal \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.49,0:14:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and offer a prayer for forgiveness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.96,0:14:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you remember something. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.96,0:14:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.30,0:14:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 23 reads: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.16,0:14:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“If, then, you are bringing \Nyour gift to the altar \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.37,0:14:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“and there you remember \Nthat your brother \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.44,0:14:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,has something against you,”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.81,0:14:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you think: \N‘My brother \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.11,0:14:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,‘does have \Nsomething against me! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.38,0:14:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,‘The last time I saw him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.38,0:14:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,‘he greeted \Neverybody else but me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.58,0:15:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He was upset. \NBut what is it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.32,0:15:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I don’t remember \Ndoing anything. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.72,0:15:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He is so sensitive! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.72,0:15:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s always upset \Nwith something.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.13,0:15:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Jesus \Nhave all of that in mind \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.39,0:15:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when he said \Nwhat he did in verse 23? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.00,0:15:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,No! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.27,0:15:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He did not go into detail \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.27,0:15:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,about what \Nthat “something” might be. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.07,0:15:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn’t say \Nwho is right or wrong. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.97,0:15:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn’t make a comment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.98,0:15:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,about whether\Nsomeone is too sensitive, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.14,0:15:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,always getting upset, \Nnever satisfied, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.08,0:15:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult to get along with. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.08,0:15:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.48,0:15:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the reason \Nbehind the “something” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.62,0:15:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is not the important thing.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.22,0:15:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the important thing? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.76,0:15:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That the peace \Nhas been disturbed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.03,0:15:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a difference \Nthat needs to be settled. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.30,0:15:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The lack of peace \Nbetween brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.77,0:15:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,could affect their relationship \Nwith Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.44,0:15:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That is important! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.71,0:15:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So what should be done?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.38,0:16:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We see the answer in verse 24: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.48,0:16:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“Leave your gift there \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.48,0:16:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“in front of the altar, \Nand go away. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.35,0:16:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“First make your peace \Nwith your brother, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.09,0:16:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and then come back \Nand offer your gift.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.16,0:16:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That animal sacrifice \Nis important too. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.66,0:16:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no doubt about that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.73,0:16:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It represents worship to Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.43,0:16:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,—like going to the meetings, \Nin the field service, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.43,0:16:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,sharing in family worship. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.57,0:16:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But according to Jesus, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.57,0:16:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,what is more important? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.77,0:16:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It is settling the difference\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.04,0:16:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,—making peace \Nwith our brother first. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.18,0:16:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we will be \Nin an acceptable position \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.38,0:16:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to offer our gift \Nof worship to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.12,0:16:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, settling differences \Nwill bring Jehovah’s favor.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.19,0:16:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But when can we apply\Nthe principle of Matthew 5? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.33,0:16:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever there is \Na difference to be settled. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.60,0:16:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps our brother \Nmisunderstood what we said or did. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.00,0:17:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Or maybe he didn’t misunderstand\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.40,0:17:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,—maybe we did give him \Na valid reason to be hurt. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.74,0:17:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Regardless, we notice \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.74,0:17:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that he has something against us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.41,0:17:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, we make peace. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.95,0:17:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We can also use \Nthe principles of this text \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.09,0:17:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,when we are hurt\Nor have something \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.55,0:17:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,against our brother. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.56,0:17:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We can take the initiative ourselves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.69,0:17:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to settle misunderstandings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.76,0:17:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to resolve differences, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.76,0:17:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and to make peace \Nwith our brother. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.80,0:17:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, Jehovah blesses \Nsuch a spirit.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.20,0:17:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, open your Bible \Nto Matthew chapter 18. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.07,0:17:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We mentioned earlier that it has \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.14,0:17:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,a more limited application. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.34,0:17:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,How so? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.35,0:17:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice verse 15: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.92,0:17:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“Moreover, \Nif your brother commits a sin, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.79,0:17:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“go and reveal his fault \Nbetween you and him alone. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.46,0:17:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If he listens to you, \Nyou have gained your brother.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.29,0:18:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Here Jesus says, \N“if your brother commits a sin.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.30,0:18:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That is much different\N than just having \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.70,0:18:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“something against [us].” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.77,0:18:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We are talking about a situation \Nthat is much more serious. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.71,0:18:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What situation? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.71,0:18:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The revised \NOrganized to Do Jehovah’s Will book, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.64,0:18:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,page 136, explains \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.68,0:18:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that it “involves financial \Nor property matters, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.42,0:18:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“such as failing to repay a loan \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.75,0:18:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“or committing fraud. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.79,0:18:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,“Or the offense \Nmight be slander, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.39,0:18:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,which seriously affects \Nsomeone’s reputation.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.39,0:18:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, \Nthey are sins that could be resolved\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.83,0:18:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,between the individuals concerned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.97,0:18:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but are also serious enough \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.17,0:18:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to merit expulsion \Nfrom the congregation if not settled.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.21,0:18:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Before we start applying \NMatthew 18:15, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.14,0:18:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we should first consider \Nwhether it is really necessary \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.35,0:18:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to pursue the matter. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.35,0:18:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Could we simply \Nforgive the individual \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.02,0:18:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,for what was done \Nor even take the loss \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.62,0:19:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,if it were a financial matter? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.16,0:19:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a personal decision.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.46,0:19:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If we decide to pursue the matter, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.93,0:19:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,what do we do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.93,0:19:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus helps us in verse 15, \Nwhen he says \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.93,0:19:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that we reveal his fault \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.94,0:19:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,between the two of us alone. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.47,0:19:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We do not discuss \Nthe matter with others, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.21,0:19:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,attempting to get them \Nto side with us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.21,0:19:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We do not go \Nstraight to the elders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.21,0:19:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and try to get them \Nto solve the problem for us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.42,0:19:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we try to resolve\Nthe matter between us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.15,0:19:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And since our goal \Nis to settle the difference, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.36,0:19:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,maintain our relationship \Nwith Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.06,0:19:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and help our brother do the same, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.53,0:19:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we make repeated efforts \Nto speak with him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.73,0:19:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,when our initial efforts \Nare unsuccessful. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.97,0:19:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep in mind \Nthat Jesus did not say: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.77,0:19:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Go only once \Nand reveal his fault.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.91,0:19:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When applying this first step, \Nmake it clear \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.38,0:19:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that your motive \Nis to ‘gain your brother.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.31,0:20:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, it would be helpful \Nto clearly state \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.92,0:20:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are applying \Nthe first step in settling differences \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.19,0:20:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,as outlined by Jesus \Nat Matthew 18:15. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.62,0:20:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, \Nthis would be stated in a kindly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.23,0:20:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,nonthreatening manner \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.23,0:20:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,but still in a way \Nto show the seriousness \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.83,0:20:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of getting the matter settled.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.13,0:20:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What if the first step \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.14,0:20:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in gaining your brother\Nis unsuccessful? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.14,0:20:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice verse 16 explains step 2: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.24,0:20:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“But if he does not listen, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.71,0:20:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“take along with you \None or two more, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.98,0:20:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that on the testimony \Nof two or three witnesses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.72,0:20:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,every matter \Nmay be established.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.72,0:20:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we talk with him \Nin the company of one or two more. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.09,0:20:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Would that be our best friends? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.83,0:20:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.96,0:20:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole purpose \Nis to ‘gain our brother.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.63,0:20:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Teaming up with two \Nof our best friends \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.17,0:20:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,could alienate our brother. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.30,0:20:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, it makes sense \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.71,0:21:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that we would choose \Nother mature Christians. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.04,0:21:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,How would mature Christians \Nbe helpful? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.05,0:21:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, are we \Nmisunderstanding things? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.25,0:21:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Could they help him \Nto reason about the matter? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.52,0:21:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Could a solution be found? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.39,0:21:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Having spiritually\Nmature witnesses there \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.79,0:21:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,may help to resolve the matter. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.26,0:21:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Generally, applying steps 1 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.80,0:21:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and 2 will result \Nin gaining your brother \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.00,0:21:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and preserving the peace \Nof the congregation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.74,0:21:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If he does not respond \Nto these repeated efforts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.01,0:21:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to help him, then what? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.58,0:21:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a decision to make. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.08,0:21:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you willing \Nto forgive your brother, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.48,0:21:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,even take a loss \Nif a financial matter is involved? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.12,0:21:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If you choose \Nto pursue the matter further, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.96,0:21:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,listen to Jesus’ words recorded \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.09,0:21:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,at verse 17: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.09,0:21:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“If he does not listen to them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.00,0:21:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“speak to the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.06,0:21:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“If he does not listen \Neven to the congregation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.40,0:22:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“let him be to you \Njust as a man of the nations \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.74,0:22:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and as a tax collector.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.07,0:22:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point, \Nthe body of elders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.94,0:22:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,representing the congregation \Nwill get involved. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.35,0:22:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They will review \Nthe facts of the case and determine \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.48,0:22:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,if a judicial committee \Nshould be appointed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.55,0:22:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Happily, though, \Nthese situations are rare, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.36,0:22:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and matters \Nare often resolved peacefully \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.89,0:22:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,before reaching \Nsuch a serious point.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.96,0:22:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Think back again \Nto that heartfelt prayer to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.90,0:22:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Has Jehovah heard \Nour sincere requests? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.70,0:22:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Will he forgive? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.91,0:22:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, at this moment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.91,0:22:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,if you realize there is a difference \Nwith your brother \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.25,0:22:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that needs to be settled, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.25,0:22:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,pray to Jehovah about the matter. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.55,0:22:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask him to help you see \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.55,0:22:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond the emotion \Nand make peace. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.75,0:22:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not let any more time go by!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.93,0:23:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we have followed \Nthe simple steps outlined by Jesus \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.33,0:23:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and have forgiven others, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.33,0:23:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the condition has been met; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.53,0:23:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the price has been paid. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.94,0:23:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what will Jehovah \Ndo for us? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.34,0:23:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.34,0:23:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He will also forgive us.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.74,0:23:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, \Nwe will gain the peace of mind \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.08,0:23:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that comes with a clean conscience, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.62,0:23:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing that we have \NJehovah’s favor and blessing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.22,0:23:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We can then \Nmake a valuable contribution \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.59,0:23:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to the beautiful, \Nunited brotherhood \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.46,0:23:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are privileged \Nto be a part of.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.53,0:23:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There are more lessons \Nin Matthew chapter 18 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.20,0:23:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that teach us how to maintain peace \Nand unity with our brothers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.70,0:23:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as important \Nas settling differences, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.48,0:23:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus cautioned against becoming \Na cause for stumbling. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.65,0:23:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,At a Bethel morning worship, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.32,0:23:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Stephen Lett described \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.32,0:23:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,three ways \Nwe can avoid stumbling others.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.19,0:24:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this word picture \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.22,0:24:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of someone being stumbled \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.46,0:24:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is quite vivid, isn’t it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.46,0:24:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve all seen someone stumbled. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.53,0:24:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, we’ve all stumbled \Nourselves at times, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.00,0:24:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and there are varying degrees \Nof consequences. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.94,0:24:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \Na person can stumble, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.67,0:24:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,quickly recover, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.67,0:24:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and continue \Nalmost uneventfully down the path. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.41,0:24:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Or a person can stumble, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.01,0:24:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,fall, break a bone, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.42,0:24:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually they recover\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.62,0:24:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,—but only after extensive therapy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.29,0:24:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Then again, a person can stumble, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.89,0:24:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,fall, hit his head, \Nnever recover\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.43,0:24:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,—becoming a casualty. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.10,0:24:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the situation is similar \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.57,0:24:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,when one is stumbled spiritually. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.37,0:24:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He can recover quickly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.77,0:24:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe recover over time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.17,0:24:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,or he may never recover\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.31,0:24:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,—becoming a spiritual casualty. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.21,0:25:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So we cannot know \Nthe ultimate outcome \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.15,0:25:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,for someone who is stumbled. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.22,0:25:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So no wonder we’re cautioned \Nto be very careful \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.89,0:25:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to never be any cause \Nfor stumbling.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.76,0:25:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Open up \Nto Matthew chapter 18, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.43,0:25:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and here’s \Nan especially powerful scripture \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.50,0:25:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in this regard. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.50,0:25:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew 18:6, Jesus says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.73,0:25:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“But whoever stumbles \None of these little ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.27,0:25:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“who have faith in me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.47,0:25:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“it would be better for him \Nto have hung around his neck \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.88,0:25:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“a millstone \Nthat is turned by a donkey \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.21,0:25:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and to be sunk in the open sea.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.18,0:25:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, with graphic language, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.45,0:25:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus describes \Nhow that if we cause someone \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.23,0:25:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to become a spiritual casualty, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.56,0:25:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,we could actually bring \Neternal doom \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.83,0:25:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,upon ourselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.83,0:25:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, here’s a question, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.83,0:25:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What could we do \Nto cause someone to stumble? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.37,0:25:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, interestingly, \Nthere are several similarities \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.51,0:26:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,between causing someone \Nto stumble physically \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.31,0:26:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and causing someone \Nto stumble spiritually.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.18,0:26:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us discuss three. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.31,0:26:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now one, pushing someone \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.85,0:26:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,could cause them to stumble, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.85,0:26:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,especially if they’re on uneven terrain, \Nif you think about it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.02,0:26:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is true \Nphysically and spiritually. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.26,0:26:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But think about Jehovah \Nfor a moment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.43,0:26:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He could push any of us, \Ncouldn’t he? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.73,0:26:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He could force us to serve him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.00,0:26:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He certainly has the power, \Nbut he never uses it that way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.94,0:26:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, he invites, he encourages; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.88,0:26:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and he explains the blessings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.94,0:26:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the curses, \Ndepending upon how we decide. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.95,0:26:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But it’s up to us, isn’t it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.42,0:26:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, at Isaiah 48:18, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.49,0:26:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah says: ‘If only \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.55,0:26:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,‘you would pay attention \Nto my commandments! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.62,0:26:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Then your peace \Nwould become like a river \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.63,0:26:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and your righteousness \Nlike the waves of the sea.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.77,0:27:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Beseeching, but not forcing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.10,0:27:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now think about it, \Nif Jehovah doesn’t force, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.34,0:27:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,he doesn’t want us \Nto force either, does he? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.61,0:27:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, parents \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.08,0:27:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,need to be very careful \Nthey don’t just simply push \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.91,0:27:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,their children to serve Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.98,0:27:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But rather, lovingly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.98,0:27:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,beseechingly like Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.05,0:27:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,try to reach the heart, \Nand of course, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.09,0:27:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,clearly show them the blessings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.12,0:27:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that will come their way \Nif they do.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.33,0:27:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Another example, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.99,0:27:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,elders should never try \Nto push Jehovah’s sheep. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.80,0:27:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard an experience \Nabout an elder, during his part, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.30,0:27:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,asked the brothers \Nfor a show of hands \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.14,0:27:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,how many were going out in service \Nthe next morning. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.81,0:27:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, only a few raised their hand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.41,0:27:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He proceeded \Nto scold the congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.41,0:27:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that more should be going out. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.75,0:27:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he then unwisely asked\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.28,0:27:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,for another show of hands. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.29,0:27:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You guessed it\N—fewer raised their hand \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.05,0:27:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the second time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.06,0:27:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Take another example, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.09,0:27:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,those who conduct Bible studies \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.63,0:28:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,should not just try to push \Ntheir students to do the right thing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.03,0:28:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“You’ve got to quit smoking! \NYou’ve got to get rid of those idols!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.60,0:28:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not with external pressure, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.14,0:28:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but by motivating their hearts, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.74,0:28:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you motivate your students.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.41,0:28:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Or take another example, \Nnone of us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.64,0:28:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,should try to push schoolmates, \Nworkmates, or relatives \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.12,0:28:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to accept the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.12,0:28:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A pushing approach, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.92,0:28:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,shoving approach\N—even though motivated with sincerity—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.79,0:28:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,has actually resulted \Nin people being stumbled \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.99,0:28:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,away from the truth \Nfor many years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.19,0:28:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes me think of the story, \Nor the saying, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.33,0:28:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that when a person \Nfirst learns the truth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.00,0:28:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you should lock them up \Nfor about six months \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.80,0:28:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to contain, or minimize, \Nthe damage they do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.77,0:28:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that saying is totally erroneous. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.98,0:28:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn’t lock that brother up; \Nyou should follow that brother. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.98,0:28:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,See, that brother has zeal, \Ndoesn’t he? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.98,0:28:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But it’s true, \Nwe probably do need to help him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.42,0:28:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to properly channel that zeal, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.42,0:29:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so that he doesn’t try \Nto force his relatives \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.92,0:29:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,or others to accept the truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.03,0:29:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that he is so excited about.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.76,0:29:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, what is the second thing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.50,0:29:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,we can do to cause someone \Nto stumble? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.37,0:29:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Placing an obstacle in their path. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.31,0:29:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now again, this is true \Nphysically or spiritually. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.11,0:29:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you think about it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.14,0:29:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,whether we put \Nthat stumbling block there intentionally \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.08,0:29:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,or unintentionally, \Nthe result is the same, isn’t it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.55,0:29:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,As mentioned \Nin today’s Watchtower comments, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.42,0:29:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,wholesome speech and upright conduct \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.16,0:29:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,can help us to avoid \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.16,0:29:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,ever being a cause for stumbling. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.66,0:29:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In contrast, unwholesome speech, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.26,0:29:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,unclean conduct, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.27,0:29:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,can easily stumble ones inside \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.34,0:29:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or outside the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.40,0:29:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, what about in an area \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.71,0:29:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,where we have a Scriptural right \Nto do something? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.78,0:29:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, surely exercising that right, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.65,0:29:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,if it stumbles someone, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.65,0:30:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,we can’t be held accountable \Nfor that, can we? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.25,0:30:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, open up \Nto 1 Corinthians chapter 8, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.29,0:30:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and here\N—very interestingly—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.46,0:30:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,this scripture \Nanswers that question. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.93,0:30:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,1 Corinthians 8:9, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.53,0:30:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,it says: \N“But keep watching \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.17,0:30:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“that your right to choose \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.77,0:30:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“does not somehow \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.90,0:30:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,become a stumbling block \Nto those who are weak.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.01,0:30:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that interesting? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.01,0:30:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Even our right to choose, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.01,0:30:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,if it would stumble someone, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.15,0:30:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we wouldn’t exercise that right \Naccording to this scripture. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.35,0:30:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle Paul, \Nin verse 13 of that same chapter, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.95,0:30:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,he said he \Nwouldn’t even eat meat ever again \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.96,0:30:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,if it stumbled his brother. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.03,0:30:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, like Paul, \Nare we willing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.03,0:30:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to forgo our rights regarding, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.63,0:30:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,for example, \Nwearing a beard, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.83,0:30:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,wearing heavy makeup, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.10,0:30:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,using alcohol\N—as just a few examples—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.04,0:30:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,if exercising that right \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.11,0:31:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,might even possibly stumble someone?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.18,0:31:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, \Nwhat’s the third way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.18,0:31:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,we could cause someone to stumble? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.71,0:31:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Failing to warn him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.32,0:31:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,about a potential trip hazard. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.85,0:31:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We could call this \Nthe sin of omission. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.59,0:31:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And again, \Nit applies physically and spiritually. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.33,0:31:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,As a physical example, \Nlet’s say we see the floor \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.33,0:31:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,has just been mopped, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.36,0:31:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and an unsuspecting person \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.17,0:31:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is approaching that wet area. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.77,0:31:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now will we warn them? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.77,0:31:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don’t warn them\N—they fall, hurt themselves—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.91,0:31:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,would we not share \Nsome responsibility? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.05,0:31:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, similarly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.05,0:31:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,with spiritual application, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.35,0:31:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Galatians 6:1 tells us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.55,0:31:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that if someone “takes a false step” \Nbefore he’s aware of it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.69,0:31:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,what are we supposed \Nto try to do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.02,0:31:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“Try to readjust” such a person, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.83,0:31:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but then it adds: \N“In a spirit of mildness.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.16,0:31:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t push him! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.00,0:32:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But try to gently, lovingly warn \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.64,0:32:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and readjust that person.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.84,0:32:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So there we have three areas \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.31,0:32:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in which we must be careful \Nwe never contribute \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.51,0:32:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,toward someone being stumbled. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.88,0:32:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t push others \Nto serve Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.28,0:32:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We strive to never, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.99,0:32:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,even unintentionally, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.15,0:32:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,put a stumbling block in their path\N—for example—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.09,0:32:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,by insisting on exercising \Nour personal rights. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.96,0:32:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And number three, \Nwe never fail to lovingly warn \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.90,0:32:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,one whom we see approaching \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.77,0:32:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,a potential trip hazard. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.64,0:32:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than being \Nany cause for stumbling, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.31,0:32:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to be \Na force for good, don’t we? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.91,0:32:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Helping others to stand firm \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.38,0:32:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and even helping ones get up \Nif they have fallen.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.12,0:32:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,None of us want to cause \Nour brother to stumble, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.72,0:32:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but it can happen \Nif we’re not careful. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.52,0:32:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not recall the three ways \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.52,0:32:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Lett listed \Nto avoid stumbling others? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.66,0:33:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You can then examine \Nhow you’re doing as a parent, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.93,0:33:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,an elder, a Bible teacher, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.33,0:33:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or as a fellow worshipper \Nin the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.30,0:33:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The effort we make toward unity \Nis always worthwhile. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.11,0:33:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We want only joyful memories \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.18,0:33:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,of the years spent \Nworking side by side \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.85,0:33:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,with our brothers and sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.05,0:33:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the way \NSister Esther Lozano looks back \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.38,0:33:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,on 73 years \Nof special full-time service.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.19,0:33:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, everybody here \Ncalls me Honey, but my name \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.76,0:33:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is Esther Lozano. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.63,0:33:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was born in Fresno, California, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.10,0:33:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in 1919. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.37,0:33:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I was baptized in 1935, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.61,0:33:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and I’ve thoroughly enjoyed \Nmy service to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.58,0:33:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I became a special pioneer, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.75,0:33:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they called me to Gilead. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.92,0:33:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in the fourth class of Gilead. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.65,0:34:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That was in 1944. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.82,0:34:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,When I left my assignment as a special, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.99,0:34:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t even know how it was to study, \Nbut this was beautiful \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.60,0:34:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,how Gilead prepared us \Nfor what was in the future. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.43,0:34:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Right after Gilead, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.84,0:34:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we went to Brooklyn Bethel for two years\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.27,0:34:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,—Esther Lopez and I—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.58,0:34:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,then I was sent to Mexico.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.81,0:34:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I came in 1947, \Nand I’m still here. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.08,0:34:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So that makes more than 68 years \NI’ve been in Mexico. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.79,0:34:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,When I arrived,\Nthere were 7 Bethelites, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.29,0:34:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and there were 22 missionaries. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.29,0:34:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We all lived right at the branch; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.30,0:34:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a branch-missionary home. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.83,0:34:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The progress in Mexico \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.27,0:34:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,really is because of the families \Nbeing united. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.94,0:34:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you get \Nthe husband and wife together, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.64,0:34:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,then the whole family \Ncomes in the truth.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.68,0:35:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1961, Sister Esther Lozano \Npreached to our grandparents. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.69,0:35:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,My grandfather first got interested \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.85,0:35:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,through the book\NFrom Paradise Lost to Paradise Regained.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.29,0:35:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When I placed the book \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.36,0:35:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with his wife\Nand she gave it to him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.19,0:35:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,he decided that that’s what \Nhe was looking for. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.13,0:35:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, \N“Well, when can I be baptized?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.47,0:35:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Three visits later, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.70,0:35:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,a study was started\Nwith the entire family.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.04,0:35:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And the oldest son was only 13. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.64,0:35:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, \N“I’m getting baptized too!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.65,0:35:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,About a year ago, he came \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.08,0:35:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and brought me a letter \Nand told me how happy he was \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.59,0:35:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that I had gone to their home \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.92,0:35:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and preached to them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.89,0:35:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was \Na happy experience of my life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.36,0:35:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, in our family, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.73,0:35:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,we are 23 Witnesses \Nspread over four generations, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.77,0:35:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and now my brother \Nand I are serving here\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.07,0:35:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,at the Central America branch.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.54,0:36:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I forgot to talk about my husband. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.71,0:36:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He was the branch overseer at that time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.61,0:36:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We were there \Nin the same branch for five years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.92,0:36:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We got to know each other, \Nbut I didn’t pay attention to him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.89,0:36:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because I was always in the service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.92,0:36:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And so,\NI don’t know when he decided \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.19,0:36:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,he wanted to get married \Nbecause I know \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.76,0:36:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that wasn’t his goal in life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.93,0:36:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I wrote Brother Knorr \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.70,0:36:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and asked him if he was surprised \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.74,0:36:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to hear that we \Nwere going to be married. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.74,0:36:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he did write me back \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.44,0:36:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and also said, \Nwell this is what he said in the letter: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.81,0:36:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You’re always jolly \Nand talkative when I’m around. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.25,0:36:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,‘On the other hand, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.31,0:36:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Brother Lozano is so quiet. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.15,0:36:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I must say,\Nit is an interesting combination. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.56,0:36:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Both of you together \Ncan serve him and aid \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.16,0:36:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,one another in your true worship.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.16,0:36:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This is one of my greatest treasures, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.63,0:37:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,having that letter from Brother Knorr.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.40,0:37:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Then when Rudy died, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.94,0:37:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t dwell on that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.77,0:37:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I remembered \NI made my dedication to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.91,0:37:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and I know that he would want me\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.45,0:37:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to put that first in my life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.45,0:37:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So I did not really suffer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.29,0:37:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that much about his death \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.35,0:37:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,because I became even more involved \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.19,0:37:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in theocratic activities.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.33,0:37:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m in the Correspondence. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.60,0:37:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But I’m at work \Nabout an hour and a half in the morning \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.10,0:37:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and an hour and a half \Nin the afternoon \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.11,0:37:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and the rest of the time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.51,0:37:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m studying here in the room. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.28,0:37:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m so pleased that I’m still able \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.61,0:37:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to go to the morning text, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.12,0:37:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and I have a part in the service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.79,0:37:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I have two studies \Nthat I conduct every week.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.49,0:38:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s such a pleasure\Nto be with people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.33,0:38:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that have dedicated\Ntheir lives to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.00,0:38:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s what makes me happy \Nbecause I know \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.40,0:38:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah counts them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.67,0:38:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as his precious sons and daughters.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.88,0:38:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t know why, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.65,0:38:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but many of the missionaries \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.38,0:38:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,have come up to me and told me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.02,0:38:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that I’ve been \Nan encouragement to them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.22,0:38:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and really, \Nthey are the ones that encourage me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.56,0:38:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s because I had \Nsuch beautiful examples \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.19,0:38:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to follow in all these years.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.53,0:38:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And all I can say \Nis thanks to Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.20,0:38:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for this great privilege \Nof serving him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.71,0:38:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Lozano is a beautiful example \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.25,0:38:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of sticking to your assignment \Nand building \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.52,0:38:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,close bonds of friendship. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.92,0:39:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice \Nanother blessing she enjoyed? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.06,0:39:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It was finding a marriage mate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.06,0:39:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,who shared her goals \Nfor full-time service.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.46,0:39:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, \Nnot every courtship leads to marriage. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.27,0:39:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’re dating, \Ncan you look past your emotions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.00,0:39:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to honestly see the differences \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.47,0:39:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and flaws \Nin your potential mate? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.28,0:39:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you accept these? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.34,0:39:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Or are they serious enough \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.35,0:39:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,for you to end your courtship? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.55,0:39:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the situation \Ndepicted in the third \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.15,0:39:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and final part of the series \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.35,0:39:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Preparing for Marriage.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.83,0:39:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the big day finally arrived.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.10,0:39:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,After all those months of preparation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.76,0:39:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it was just as I imagined.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.50,0:39:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh wait! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.17,0:39:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s not me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.70,0:39:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.61,0:40:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As I watched my sister \Nget married that day, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.12,0:40:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t help \Nbut think about my own future.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.23,0:40:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When I began dating Shane, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.57,0:40:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,everything was perfect.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.63,0:40:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We spent a lot of time \Ntalking on the phone.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.18,0:41:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything just naturally \Nseemed to click.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.63,0:41:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was convinced he was the one.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.32,0:41:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But over time, \NI started to notice some things.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.67,0:42:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was starting to see patterns.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.39,0:42:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And they didn’t seem \Nto be getting better.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.59,0:43:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn’t even sure \Nour goals were the same anymore.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.71,0:43:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt alone. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.25,0:43:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But thankfully, I wasn’t.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.46,0:43:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom kindly asked \Nhow things were going, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.86,0:43:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,so I told her.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.70,0:43:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“Maybe he’s not the one,” \NI told her.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.30,0:43:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought she was going to tell me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.77,0:43:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,which way I should go, \Nbut she didn’t. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.31,0:43:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, she reassured me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.98,0:43:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that if he wasn’t the one, \NI was going to be OK.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.00,0:44:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They reminded me about what Jesus said \Nwhen building a tower. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.58,0:44:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“For example, who of you \Nwanting to build a tower \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.91,0:44:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“does not first sit down \Nand calculate the expense \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.18,0:44:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to see if he has enough \Nto complete it?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.99,0:44:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that I was about to enter \Ninto a building project of my own\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.53,0:44:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,—my relationship with Shane—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.53,0:44:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and I too needed \Nto “calculate the expense” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.23,0:44:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,before I commit to it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.83,0:44:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They encouraged me \Nto talk to Shane \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.40,0:44:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell him about the things \Nthat were concerning me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.21,0:44:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So I did.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.79,0:45:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And my mom was right. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.19,0:45:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I was OK, more than OK, really.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.72,0:45:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Shane and I decided it was best \Nto break off the relationship.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.37,0:45:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And some years later,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.03,0:45:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I found someone \Nthat loves Jehovah as much as I do, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.51,0:45:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and I love him with my whole heart.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.15,0:45:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Our sister wisely compared \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.32,0:45:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,her relationship \Nto a building project. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.05,0:45:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,She “calculated the expense” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.22,0:45:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of any traits she saw \Nduring their courtship\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.96,0:45:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,—well before they \Ncould become problems in a marriage. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.76,0:45:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, \Nwe shouldn’t expect \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.90,0:45:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,perfection from our mate, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.93,0:45:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but working through matters \Nduring courtship \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.70,0:45:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is another opportunity \Nthat Jehovah provides \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.37,0:46:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to settle differences in peace.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.78,0:46:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s something common \Nto every successful marriage \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.65,0:46:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,between two Christians. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.68,0:46:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It is their putting Jehovah first \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.88,0:46:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and supporting \Neach other’s personal dedication to God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.49,0:46:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This is certainly true \Nwith Viv and Ann Mouritz, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.09,0:46:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,serving \Nin the Australasia branch. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.03,0:46:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They’ve been married\Nfor 65 years \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.23,0:46:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and have \Na combined 131 years \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.23,0:46:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in full-time service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.30,0:46:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to their advice \Nfor younger ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.30,0:46:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,deciding what to do \Nin Jehovah’s organization.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.28,0:46:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I started pioneering \Nin November 1948. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.81,0:46:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s a while ago now. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.81,0:46:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s what I thought \NI would do—pioneer.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.15,0:46:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said, “Well, Jehovah, \Nif I do what you ask me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.29,0:46:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“I accept whatever assignment \Nyou give me,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.36,0:46:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“and I’ll just go \Nwhere you send me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.43,0:46:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and I won’t seek an assignment, \Nbut I won’t refuse one.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.47,0:47:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s all I intended to do \Nas far as I knew, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.00,0:47:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but then I had only been pioneering \Nabout a year \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.34,0:47:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,when I got this envelope, \Nand the letter said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.47,0:47:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“Please fill in the enclosed form.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.88,0:47:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It was an application for Bethel, \Nand I thought, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.08,0:47:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Goodness, I didn’t think of Bethel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.08,0:47:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I told Jehovah I’d go where he sent me, \Nso don’t argue, just do it.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.95,0:47:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I was working in the printery \Ncleaning out old ink tins \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.42,0:47:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and making schedules \Nfor printing and so on. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.23,0:47:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I got to work \Non the press too, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.30,0:47:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but I wasn’t there very long \Nwhen they moved me to the office.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.57,0:47:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you learn a lot in Bethel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.77,0:47:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You learn how to live \Nwith your brothers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.77,0:47:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,which you’re not used to. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.77,0:47:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You learn about Jehovah’s organization\N—you see how it operates. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.58,0:47:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the privilege of working alongside \Nbrothers who had lots of experience.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.49,0:47:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I got assigned \Nto Metropolitan Congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.69,0:47:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s where Ann was.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.69,0:47:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we got married \Nin October 1951, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.73,0:48:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and two weeks later, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.73,0:48:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I started pioneering.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.70,0:48:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I was 20 at that time \Nwhen we started circuit work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.67,0:48:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and I’d only pioneered for a year; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.54,0:48:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,so of course I was very worried \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.04,0:48:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and scared about having to witness \Nwith sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.88,0:48:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that had pioneered for years \Nand some of them even of the anointed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.82,0:48:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I cried halfway to Melbourne.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.75,0:48:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We got very close \Nto the brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.56,0:48:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and especially to the children, \Nso we really loved that.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.56,0:48:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we \Ngot the opportunity to go\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.86,0:48:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to New York \Nto the international convention \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.20,0:48:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in 1958. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.60,0:48:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,When the Society found out \Nwe were going, they sent us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.21,0:48:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,an application for Gilead, \Nand we thought, ‘Oh, my goodness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.34,0:48:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we do that?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.58,0:48:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So we said, \N“Well, we don’t say no.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.22,0:48:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,After the ‘58 convention, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.55,0:49:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,we were assigned to special pioneer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.09,0:49:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,in Canada for six months. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.29,0:49:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Knorr said \Nwe were in cold storage, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.43,0:49:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so there were about 40 of us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.56,0:49:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,from British Commonwealth countries. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.86,0:49:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was a good experience too. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.43,0:49:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw winter for the first time. \NI did, anyway.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.47,0:49:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And we took pictures \Nof snow and ice and icicles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.87,0:49:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to show in our assignment when we \Ngot into India or Africa or somewhere. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.34,0:49:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah had a sense of humor; \Nhe sent us to Finland.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.58,0:49:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the schooling you get from Gilead \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.79,0:49:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,or the other schools \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.79,0:49:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,helps you to see Jehovah’s organization \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.26,0:49:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it works.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.53,0:49:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn’t know a lot about Finland \Nexcept that we knew it was cold \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.86,0:49:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and clean \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.20,0:49:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and a long way from Australia.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.24,0:49:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Being so far from Australia, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.01,0:49:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,we knew that we \Nwouldn’t be able to get home \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.01,0:50:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to see our families, \Nnot for a long, long time.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.75,0:50:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,When we moved into Finland, \Nthe brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.09,0:50:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,in Russia and those countries \Nwere under ban. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.66,0:50:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,They needed spiritual food, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.66,0:50:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and so it had to be supplied to them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.23,0:50:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So we used to send people in as tourists, \Nand they would meet \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.37,0:50:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the brothers there \Nand deliver the food to them.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.17,0:50:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Without Jehovah’s blessing \Nand his spirit, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.84,0:50:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we couldn’t have done it at all. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.24,0:50:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s amazing to think \Nthat the amount of spiritual food \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.98,0:50:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that got in there, \Nthey translated it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.98,0:50:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and they made it available. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.05,0:50:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And we did that for over 20 years \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.05,0:50:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,without any mishaps. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.26,0:50:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It couldn’t happen \Nwithout Jehovah’s blessing.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.69,0:50:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Leaving Finland was not easy, \Nof course. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.83,0:50:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We had mixed feelings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.63,0:50:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but, actually, \NI saw Jehovah’s hand \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.53,0:50:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in the assignment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.43,0:50:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because we really got back \Nto Australia \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.47,0:50:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,at a time when my parents \Nwere needing help, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.74,0:51:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,so we didn’t have to leave Bethel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.81,0:51:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,or full-time service \Nto give that help.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.85,0:51:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We were asked \Nto go to Russia in 1999. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.58,0:51:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That turned out \Nto be two and a half years.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.99,0:51:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a little apprehensive \Nabout going to Russia, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.39,0:51:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was really one of the most \Nmemorable assignments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.66,0:51:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ve ever had.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.33,0:51:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In Russia, the brothers \Nwere not used to house-to-house work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.73,0:51:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because of all the years under ban. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.63,0:51:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was quite different \Nbecause you go to the door; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.04,0:51:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you can’t just strike up a conversation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.34,0:51:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The person wants to know \Nwhy you are there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.34,0:51:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can’t make \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.74,0:51:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,a return visit on someone \Nyou met on the street\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.74,0:51:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,—well, you don’t know \Nwhere he lives. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.75,0:51:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’ve called at his house, you do, \Nand you can make a return visit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.62,0:51:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers saw \Nthe advantage of that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.02,0:51:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But they had to learn. \NIt was a new thing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.36,0:51:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Circuit overseers had to learn \Nhow to visit congregations, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.49,0:51:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and Polish brothers came in \Nand helped a lot with that\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.23,0:51:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,—did circuit work—\Nbut they too had to learn. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.40,0:52:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was a big change for them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.40,0:52:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to come from working \Nunder ban all their lives \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.14,0:52:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to now working the way \Nthe rest of the world does.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.48,0:52:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The best decision I ever made \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.51,0:52:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,was to put my life \Nin Jehovah’s hands, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.78,0:52:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and to say, “You decide \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.85,0:52:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,where I go and what I do.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.19,0:52:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve had the feeling all along, \Nand it’s proven true so far, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.52,0:52:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that everything I have done \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.53,0:52:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,has been training for something else. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.50,0:52:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what I’m doing now \Nis still training. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.63,0:52:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be for the new world\Nbecause I haven’t got \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.73,0:52:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,much time left in this one. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.80,0:52:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What will it be? \NWell, who knows?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.11,0:52:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So my recommendation \Nto everyone is: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.38,0:52:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t decide for yourself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.38,0:52:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let Jehovah do it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.15,0:52:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother and Sister Mouritz \Nalways looked to Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.75,0:52:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,for their assignments. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.75,0:52:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,For Brother Mouritz, \Nthat’s meant serving \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.22,0:53:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,on the Branch Committees \Nin Finland, India, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.19,0:53:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Russia, Poland, Ukraine, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.63,0:53:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and Australasia \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.63,0:53:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and the privilege of making visits \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.63,0:53:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to more than 70 countries \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.64,0:53:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,as a representative \Nof world headquarters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.77,0:53:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We can certainly pursue \Nany form of service \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.38,0:53:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that our circumstances allow. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.44,0:53:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But when we pray \Nfor Jehovah’s direction, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.45,0:53:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,we rely on him to send us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.45,0:53:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,where it benefits his organization \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.72,0:53:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and ourselves the most.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.12,0:53:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The willing spirit \Nto do Jehovah’s will \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.86,0:53:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is shared by Bethelites \Nwho have received \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.06,0:53:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,new assignments in the field. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.39,0:53:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Adjustments in the work at Bethel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.83,0:53:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,have put greater emphasis \Non the preaching work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.00,0:53:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,More resources, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.00,0:53:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,including experienced Bible teachers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.87,0:53:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,are being directed \Nto the busy harvest. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.04,0:53:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In this report \Nfrom the South Africa branch, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.08,0:53:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,we hear from loyal ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.08,0:53:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,who are supporting theocratic direction.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.55,0:54:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,On September 23, 2015, \Nit was announced \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.62,0:54:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,at all branches that \Nthe Governing Body was requesting \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.79,0:54:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,all Bethel families to reduce in size.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.00,0:54:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,For me personally, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.33,0:54:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,when they made that announcement \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.73,0:54:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,on Wednesday, September 23, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.33,0:54:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that was exciting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.97,0:54:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It was—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.94,0:54:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it was momentous.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.50,0:54:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,When the announcement was made, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.51,0:54:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,tears welled up in my eyes\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.81,0:54:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,because I realized how close we are\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.31,0:54:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to the end. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.34,0:54:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember just closing my eyes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.91,0:54:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and saying to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.95,0:54:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“Whatever you want, we’ll do.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.18,0:54:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,When I received news of my reassignment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.35,0:54:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,initially I was numb.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.35,0:54:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,When I got the news \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.99,0:54:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,about my reassignment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.86,0:54:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so scared in the beginning.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.63,0:54:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It caught me off guard. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.79,0:54:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn’t expecting it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.36,0:54:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We were quite shocked and sad, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.97,0:54:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but we were encouraged by the brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.70,0:54:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,at Bethel and also in the congregation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.21,0:54:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The direction from the Governing Body\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.11,0:54:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,was that we were being reassigned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.48,0:54:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,as regular pioneers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.98,0:55:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We signed the forms for pioneering \Nthat very Thursday.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.82,0:55:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,For me, I’ve always appreciated \Nthe scripture at 1 Samuel 12:22 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.15,0:55:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,where it states there: \N“For the sake of his great name, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.29,0:55:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will not abandon his people.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.39,0:55:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t want to forget my Bethel time,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.23,0:55:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was lovely, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.53,0:55:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but I want to stretch forward ahead \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.16,0:55:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to pioneering and really enjoy it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.73,0:55:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We prayed specifically for a place \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.57,0:55:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that is going to help us \Nto be as simple\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.47,0:55:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,as possible so that we can focus \Nour attention to the ministry.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.51,0:55:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All that I’d love to say \Nto everyone who has been reassigned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.15,0:55:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is that Jehovah is our Father, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.81,0:55:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and he will never relinquish \Nhis responsibility as a Father. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.98,0:55:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He will take care of us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.05,0:55:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We are losing four couples \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.02,0:55:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,from our congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.99,0:55:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And I would like to tell \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.99,0:55:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the congregations \Nwhere they have been assigned to \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.83,0:55:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that they are getting \Nreal spiritual people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.06,0:55:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and that they are \Nreally going to be an asset \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.77,0:55:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to their congregation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.07,0:55:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to also thank \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.07,0:56:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the brothers in the congregation \Nwhere we are going to \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.51,0:56:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because they organized \Nsecular work for us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.58,0:56:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and also, as Bonnie mentioned, \Naccommodation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.58,0:56:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So they made it easier for us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.85,0:56:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to look forward to our assignment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.25,0:56:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But we know this, \Nof course, comes from Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.35,0:56:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the Branch Committee said, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.62,0:56:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“Well, we have to move quickly with this.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.63,0:56:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We asked the family,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.73,0:56:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“Please, give us two, \Nthree weeks to work things out,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.43,0:56:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is what they appreciated. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.70,0:56:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Congregations phoned in. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.60,0:56:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bethelites were offered jobs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.24,0:56:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They were offered accommodation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.07,0:56:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Our congregation is delighted \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.47,0:56:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,having two young Bethelites\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.04,0:56:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,coming and joining us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.08,0:56:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Our congregation \Nhas quite a number of young people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.65,0:56:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We can already see that \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.92,0:56:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s going to benefit them quite a lot. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.32,0:56:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve actually assisted them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.25,0:56:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,in getting a place \Nwhere they could stay, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.25,0:56:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and also we’ve assisted them \Nto settle in\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.29,0:56:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and be part of the congregation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.79,0:56:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to our new home! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.43,0:56:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve been here\Na little over a week now.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.33,0:56:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers helped \Nto paint the house, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.77,0:57:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to put tiles on, \Nto clean the entire place. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.14,0:57:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So they really did \Na lot of work in our behalf.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.74,0:57:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, memories \Nof our friends from Bethel.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.11,0:57:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It was about six months ago \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.28,0:57:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,when we enjoyed pioneer school.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.64,0:57:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to our brothers, \Nwe were able to find employment.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.35,0:57:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has been \Nanswering our prayers,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.52,0:57:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and sometimes \Nhe has been answering \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.95,0:57:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,our concerns \Neven before we even pray about it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.65,0:57:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.16,0:57:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,these extraordinary experiences \Nin South Africa \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.16,0:57:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,are mirrored all over the world. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.66,0:57:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The love we show \Nto each other is a reflection \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.97,0:57:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jehovah’s great love \Nfor each of us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.20,0:57:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and we thank him to be a part \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.14,0:57:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of this amazing brotherhood.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.25,0:57:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The Governing Body \Ndeeply appreciates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.68,0:57:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the brotherhood’s loyal response \Nto theocratic direction. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.39,0:57:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Change is not always easy, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.69,0:57:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but it helps when we look \Nat Jehovah’s blessing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.36,0:57:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,on new spiritual provisions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.36,0:58:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and adjustments to the work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.63,0:58:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Letters of appreciation \Nfrom our brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.50,0:58:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,add to the Governing Body’s confidence \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.63,0:58:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah \Nis directing his organization. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.34,0:58:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,A sister from the United States \Nwrote this about JW Broadcasting, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.04,0:58:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“Often the programming seems like \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.54,0:58:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,a direct answer to a prayer.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.35,0:58:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,After a particularly difficult day, \Nshe added: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.82,0:58:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“What did I find today at home \Nfor me like a present from Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.22,0:58:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The March [2016] broadcast \N. . . dealing with discouragement.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.76,0:58:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,After watching \Nthe January 2016 broadcast, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.63,0:58:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,a family from Austria wrote: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.20,0:58:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Our eldest son is serving \Nin the branch in Selters, Germany. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.71,0:58:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,‘We are very proud of him, \Nbut we terribly miss him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.84,0:58:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,‘So we love the new song, \N“I Give You My Best.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.98,0:58:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,‘It’s heartwarming \Nthat you know our feelings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.72,0:59:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and value our offers.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.05,0:59:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is certainly giving us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.56,0:59:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,what we need \Nwhen we need it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.23,0:59:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And it comes to us \Nin such variety. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.43,0:59:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This next music video, \Nfor example, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.56,0:59:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,fits well with our discussion \Non settling differences. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.24,0:59:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It begins with a situation \Nbetween a young mother \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.61,0:59:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and her mother-in-law \Nand reminds us\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.47,0:59:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,, to “Forgive One Another.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.12,0:59:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you had the best of intentions.\NKindnesses too numerous to mention.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.54,0:59:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But thoughtless words \Njust cut me to the heart.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.58,1:00:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, as a tear appears, I see.\NThings aren’t what they seem to be.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.29,1:00:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Before the sun slips from the sky,\NLet’s be sure we both see eye to eye.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.26,1:00:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll forget the things we said,\NAnd, please, let’s forgive.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.37,1:00:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Sisters today, sisters we’ll stay.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.84,1:00:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting along is not always easy.\NAngry words can bring you down, believe me.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.56,1:00:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you find a reason to forgive,\NAnd now you realize it’s true;\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.87,1:00:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Letting go’s the thing to do.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.04,1:01:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Before the sun slips from the sky,\NLet’s be sure we both see eye to eye.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.25,1:01:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll forget the things we said,\NAnd, please, let’s forgive.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.89,1:01:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers today, brothers we’ll stay.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.10,1:01:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Not one thing said or done can break us up. \NLove’s a bond of unity.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.81,1:01:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Cancel the debt; forgive and forget.\NThat’s the way true friendship should be.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.92,1:02:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Before the sun slips from the sky,\NLet’s be sure we both see eye to eye.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.20,1:02:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll forget the things we said,\NAnd, please, let’s forgive.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.98,1:02:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Here in our hearts, that’s where it starts.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.42,1:02:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Bonded in love, forgiving one another.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.30,1:02:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see two critical areas \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.11,1:02:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,where we need to be forgiving? \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.24,1:02:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It was in the family \Nand in the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.98,1:02:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll always have reasons \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.98,1:02:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in this imperfect world \Nto forgive. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.45,1:02:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Look for the opportunities \Nin your life \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.85,1:02:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to imitate Jehovah \Nand forgive others.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.99,1:02:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,As we conclude our program, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.99,1:02:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we take you on a visit \Nto world headquarters \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.73,1:03:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in Warwick, New York. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.73,1:03:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bethel family \Nhas been moving \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.00,1:03:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,into their new work areas. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.13,1:03:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,More than 25,000 brothers \Nand sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.30,1:03:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,worked on the construction \Nof the facility. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.14,1:03:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a united effort \Nby temporary volunteers, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.08,1:03:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,construction servants, \NBethelites, construction groups, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.01,1:03:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and volunteers \Nwho previously worked \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.35,1:03:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,on Kingdom Hall projects. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.75,1:03:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier this year, \Nworkers were making \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.15,1:03:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,final preparations for the arrival \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.16,1:03:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of world headquarters staff. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.63,1:03:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,When open for tours, \Nvisitors will enjoy \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.23,1:03:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the historic Bible display, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.36,1:03:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,a visual history exhibit \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.97,1:03:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and an interactive museum \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.24,1:03:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,explaining how Jehovah directs \Nhis organization today. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.41,1:03:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We thank Jehovah for all \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.64,1:03:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,who helped to complete \Nthe new world headquarters. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.65,1:03:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That includes \Nthe thousands of volunteers \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.78,1:03:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but also the millions \Nof you dear brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.52,1:04:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,who support the worldwide work \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.09,1:04:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,with your regular donations. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.52,1:04:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We send you our love \Nand pray for Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.19,1:04:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to bless \Nour united brotherhood. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.53,1:04:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,From Brooklyn, New York, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.53,1:04:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,this is JW Broadcasting!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.72,0:00:05.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,JW Broadcastingにようこそ！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.96,0:00:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,今月のプログラムでは\N次の点を考えます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.16,0:00:14.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,交際期間中に予期しなかった問題が\N明らかになったならどうしますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.10,0:00:17.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,“結婚に備える”シリーズの\Nパート3では—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.03,0:00:22.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,結婚を考える際にどのように\N“費用を計算”できるかが示されます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.21,0:00:26.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,オーストラリアでビブ・モリッツと\N妻のアンに会います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.21,0:00:30.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,お二人は世界中で\N全時間奉仕を行なってきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.01,0:00:32.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,神聖な奉仕を追い求めている人たちは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.85,0:00:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,お二人からどんなアドバイスを\N聞けるでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.45,0:00:38.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,このプログラムの\N主題を強調する—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.25,0:00:41.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,ミュージック・ビデオも\N楽しめるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.19,0:00:47.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹との不和を解決し\N互いに許し合うよう強められます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.20,0:00:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,では2016年10月の\NJW Broadcastingです!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.66,0:01:15.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず ウクライナからの報告です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.63,0:01:20.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,2014年 ウクライナ北部で\N政治的な緊張が高まり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.23,0:01:24.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,軍事紛争へと発展しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.17,0:01:27.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,数か月以内に7,600人以上の\Nエホバの証人が—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.70,0:01:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,避難所を求めて\N逃れる必要が生じました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.27,0:01:34.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,自宅に隠れていた人たちもいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.04,0:01:39.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちは身体的にも霊的にも\Nどのように生き延びたのでしょうか？ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.02,0:01:44.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,数百キロ離れたリボフにある支部で\N救援活動が組織されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.69,0:01:46.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のインタビューの中で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.36,0:01:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹たちは組織や互いから受けた\N愛と世話について述べています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.98,0:02:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,何の予告もなく 戦いが始まりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.82,0:02:16.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちはすぐに逃げなければ\Nなりませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.69,0:02:24.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,十分な食べ物はなく\N店にも何もありませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.86,0:02:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,薬も不足し\N水も電気もありませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.43,0:02:31.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,怖ろしかったです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.97,0:02:33.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,非常に混乱していました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.74,0:02:36.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうすれば良いか\Nわかりませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.61,0:02:39.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,留まるべきか？\Nそれとも 逃げるべきか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.81,0:02:45.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,7歳になる 三つ子の\N子どもたちがいて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.62,0:02:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,シェルターに入るとすぐ\N王国の歌を歌い始めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.86,0:02:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,大人もその歌に加わりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.16,0:02:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,おかげで外の爆音が\N気になりませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.80,0:03:05.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,食料は尽き\Nお金もありませんでしたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.80,0:03:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,切り抜けられると信じていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.50,0:03:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,神がわたしたちを飢え死に\Nさせることはないからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.58,0:03:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,撃ち合いや爆発が頻発していたので\N通常の集会は開けませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.32,0:03:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,普段のような宣教を\N組織することもできませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.22,0:03:25.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あまりにも危険だったからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.72,0:03:30.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,東部での紛争に関する\N最初の報告を受けると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.13,0:03:33.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,支部委員会は集まって\N祈りのうちに状況を分析しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.93,0:03:37.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちを 霊的また身体的に\N守るため—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.33,0:03:40.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのように助けられるか\Nエホバの知恵を求めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.94,0:03:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体にも\N最新の報告を送り続けました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.71,0:03:50.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆から 156トンの食料と\N21トンの衣服が寄せられ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.78,0:03:52.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,仲間の兄弟たちに そして—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.62,0:03:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの証人以外の人々にも\N分配されました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.19,0:04:00.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初は 5トンの救援物資を\N受け取ると聞いていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.79,0:04:04.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 5トンではなく 実際には\N15トンを受け取ったときは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.89,0:04:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当にびっくりしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.50,0:04:13.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,箱の中には 兄弟姉妹たちの書いた\Nメモも入っていて 嬉しかったです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.14,0:04:22.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,近くの都市の兄弟たちは 家を提供し\N食料を備えてくれただけでなく—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.68,0:04:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,何よりも 兄弟として\N温かく迎え入れてくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.25,0:04:31.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちを助けるため\N犠牲を払い—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.59,0:04:37.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,予定を調整し 家族の時間の幾らかさえ\N用いる覚悟でいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.33,0:04:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹が必要とするものを届けるため\N朝の6時に出かけました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.54,0:04:55.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,紛争のあった2か月半と \N復旧のための2か月の間に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.98,0:04:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,自転車で6,500キロ 走りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.75,0:05:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,スラバンスクの長老たちは\N小さな会衆を組織し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.16,0:05:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちを霊的に支えるため\N定期的に集会を開きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.56,0:05:16.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹の家屋\N20棟で大規模な修繕が—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.27,0:05:20.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,72の家屋で小規模な修繕が\N行なわれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.31,0:05:24.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,二つのプログラムが\N準備されました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.77,0:05:27.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,紛争地域だけでなく\Nウクライナ全域—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.91,0:05:31.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,そしてロシアやベラルーシの\N会衆も加わりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.55,0:05:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,出席者は\N32万5千人に及びました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.39,0:05:41.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,興味深いのは\Nエホバの証人ではない人々の反応です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.42,0:05:45.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,それぞれ自分の宗教がありますが\Nこう言うんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.76,0:05:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“皆さんだけが \N 本当に気遣いを示し—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.13,0:05:53.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,“行ないによって\N純粋な愛を表わしています”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.20,0:05:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,これこそが\N他の宗教との違いです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.48,0:06:01.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,主人も息子も—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.94,0:06:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちが利他的な愛を\N示していることに気づきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.02,0:06:11.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,主人は聖書研究を始め\N今では定期的に集会に出席しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.69,0:06:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,最近 神権宣教学校にも\N入校しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.16,0:06:20.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしはこの愛を\N個人として経験して—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.90,0:06:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟との聖書研究を再開しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.30,0:06:27.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,今 バプテスマに向けた\N準備をしています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.87,0:06:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,残念なことに\N一人の姉妹が命を落としました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.78,0:06:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,人は すべての物を失うことが\Nありますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.58,0:06:41.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の子供を失うことに比べれば\N大したことではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.98,0:06:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹は わたしたちに\N耳を傾け—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.22,0:06:47.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,共に泣いてくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.09,0:06:49.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,言葉にできないほど\N嬉しかったです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.73,0:06:52.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,まるでエホバの腕に\N抱かれているかのようでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.96,0:06:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,神は わたしたちが\N倒れるままにはされず—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.03,0:06:58.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,“愛する者よ 手を離さないで”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.47,0:07:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしがあなたを助け 支える”\Nと言っておられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.77,0:07:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの民の間に\N国境はありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.98,0:07:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,これこそ 真の宗教です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.65,0:07:17.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウクライナの兄弟たちのために\N引き続き祈りましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.25,0:07:20.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちはエホバの愛を\N確信していますし—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.06,0:07:25.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはどんな試練においても\N兄弟たちを支えてくださることでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.90,0:07:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちの世界的な兄弟関係は\N実に特別なものです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.13,0:07:35.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちが困っているとき\N何でも助けになりたいと願います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.44,0:07:38.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,また集会 野外奉仕 \Nその他どんな時でも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.61,0:07:42.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちと共にいることを\N大きな喜びと感じます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.88,0:07:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちを愛しており\N一緒に時を過ごすのは喜びです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.12,0:07:53.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,とはいえ わたしたちは不完全ですから\N愛と一致が試みられることもあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.16,0:07:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,感情を傷つけられたり\N傷つけたりすることがあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.60,0:08:01.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで今月のプログラムでは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.76,0:08:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“不和を解決してエホバの恵みを得る”\Nという主題で考えてみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.54,0:08:12.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはマタイ 6章14節に\N基づいています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.07,0:08:14.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,この重要な聖句を一緒に読みましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.84,0:08:20.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,弟子たちに祈りの仕方を教えたすぐ後\Nイエスは14節でこう述べました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.49,0:08:24.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなた方が人の罪過を許すなら—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.92,0:08:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなた方の天の父もあなた方を\N許してくださるのです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.56,0:08:32.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,この言葉はわたしたちの\N日々の崇拝に対する—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.53,0:08:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの見方にどの程度影響しますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.70,0:08:39.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは一日の終わりに\N祈ろうとしています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.97,0:08:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバのお名前が\N神聖なものとされるように\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.54,0:08:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,王国が来ますように\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.01,0:08:51.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体や指導の任に当たっている\N兄弟たちに祝福があるように\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.85,0:08:54.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,また個人的な心配事について祈ります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.75,0:08:57.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,それからこう言います—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.12,0:09:02.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,“エホバわたしは不完全で\Nたびたび罪を犯します”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.02,0:09:04.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,“どうぞ罪をお許しください”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.59,0:09:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“どうぞみ前で清く是認された立場を\Nお与えください”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.07,0:09:16.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,さて問題は エホバはあなたの\N心からの願いを聞かれるでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.87,0:09:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,許してくださいますか？ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.21,0:09:21.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは何と述べたでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.41,0:09:24.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう一度 14節を見てください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.15,0:09:26.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなた方が人の罪過を許すなら—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.78,0:09:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなた方の天の父もあなた方を\N許してくださるでしょう”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.49,0:09:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスが条件を付けていることに\Nお気づきですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.42,0:09:38.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,許しは自動的には与えられないのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.89,0:09:41.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,条件または代価が必要です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.40,0:09:43.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな代価ですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.03,0:09:46.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスによればもしわたしたちが\N“人の罪過を許すなら”—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.90,0:09:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,条件は満たされ\N代価は支払われたことになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.54,0:09:53.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはどうされますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.78,0:09:57.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなた方を許してくださる”\Nとイエスは述べました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.45,0:10:03.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,“人を許した場合に限って あなた方を許そう”\Nとエホバがわたしたちに言われるのは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.55,0:10:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,公正で道理にかなったことでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.36,0:10:12.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,では重い病気になって\N仕事を失ったと仮定してみてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.83,0:10:15.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,何か月も支払いができません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.33,0:10:17.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,切迫した状況です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.87,0:10:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほとんど打つ手がありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.34,0:10:24.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,妻や子供のことが心配です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.84,0:10:26.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで家主の所に行って—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.74,0:10:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,回復するまで猶予を\N与えてほしいと頼みます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.68,0:10:33.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,良くなって働けるようになるなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.65,0:10:37.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,負債を支払うために\N何でも行なうつもりでいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.52,0:10:41.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,家主は大丈夫と言います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.82,0:10:45.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,事情を理解し\N負債をしばらく取り消してくれたので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.80,0:10:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,状況が良くなるまで\N支払いする必要はなくなりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.87,0:10:53.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして家族を世話できるようになるまで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.30,0:10:57.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,毎月の出費も賄ってくれることに\Nなったのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.81,0:11:00.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,この人がしてくれたことをどう思いますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.84,0:11:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは他の人の扱い方に\Nどんな影響を及ぼしますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.85,0:11:07.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,罪深い傾向のゆえに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.72,0:11:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちはエホバに負債を抱えており\N死に値する者です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.59,0:11:15.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分では負債を支払えません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.12,0:11:18.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも祈りでエホバに近づき\N助けを求めるなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.89,0:11:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,大きな憐れみと親切を示して\N心配はいらないと言ってくださいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.40,0:11:29.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちの負債のために\Nみ子の命を与えてくださったのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.94,0:11:32.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはその犠牲に基づいて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.11,0:11:37.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちが日々犯す罪に対する\N支払いを喜んで行なってくださり— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.05,0:11:41.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,新しい世でわたしたちが\N完全になって回復を遂げるまで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.15,0:11:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,許しを差し伸べてくださるのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.66,0:11:48.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,マタイ 6章14節にある—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.69,0:11:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,簡潔で力強いイエスの言葉を\Nもう一度考えてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.60,0:11:56.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなた方が人の罪過を許すなら—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.07,0:12:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなた方の天の父もあなた方を\N許してくださるのです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.00,0:12:03.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは公正で\N道理にかなっていますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.51,0:12:05.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際的ですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.84,0:12:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その通りです！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.41,0:12:12.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際 不和を解決し\N惜しみなく許すことは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.08,0:12:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの同情心や憐れみ深い特質に\Nならう最善の方法です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.19,0:12:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,不和を素早く解決する\N助けがありますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.23,0:12:28.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初にすべきことは 間違いを\N愛で覆うようにすることです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.43,0:12:31.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,ただ許して忘れるのです \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.77,0:12:32.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうできるなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.97,0:12:37.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それこそ会衆の平和と一致を保つ\N素晴らしい方法となります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.74,0:12:42.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,もしなかなか忘れることが\Nできないなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.55,0:12:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,不和を解決する点で\N特に助けとなる聖句が二つあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.32,0:12:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはマタイ 5章23, 24節と\Nマタイ 18章15-17節です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.39,0:13:00.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,これらの聖句は同じ状況について\N述べているのではありませんし—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.26,0:13:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,全く同じように適用すべきものでもない\Nことを思いに留めてください \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.44,0:13:09.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,マタイ5章は適用範囲がより広く—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.14,0:13:13.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほとんどの状況で平和を保つために\N用いることができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.84,0:13:18.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,マタイ18章は適用範囲がより限定的で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.91,0:13:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,より深刻な性質の特定の状況に\N当てはめるものです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.55,0:13:29.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,では マタイ5章23, 24節を\N考慮しましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.86,0:13:33.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それで供え物を祭壇に持って来て—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.26,0:13:36.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,“兄弟が自分に対して\N何か反感を抱いていることを—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.17,0:13:40.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,“そこで思い出したならあなたの供え物を\Nそこ祭壇の前に残しておいて—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.67,0:13:42.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,”出かけて行きなさい”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.30,0:13:44.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,“まず自分の兄弟と和睦し—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.07,0:13:48.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それから戻って来たときに\Nあなたの供え物をささげなさい”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.54,0:13:52.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,これらの節が今日のわたしたちに\Nどんな意味があるのかを理解するには—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.88,0:13:56.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスの言葉が西暦１世紀の\Nユダヤ人にとって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.25,0:13:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな意味があったのかを\N理解しなければなりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.26,0:14:02.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,2千年前のエルサレムの都市に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.36,0:14:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分がいるところを\N思い描いてみてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.16,0:14:10.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,毎年開かれる祭りの\N一つに来ています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.37,0:14:13.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,そには幾万もの人でごった返しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.70,0:14:17.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは立派な子羊を\N犠牲にしようとしています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.44,0:14:19.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,一番良いものです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.21,0:14:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,きれいで傷がありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.34,0:14:27.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは子羊を携えて中庭を通り\N祭司の中庭までやって来ます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.68,0:14:30.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこまで行くのにほぼ一日がかりです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.59,0:14:36.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,やっと動物の上に手を置き罪の許しの\N祈りをささげる準備ができましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.03,0:14:38.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこであることを思い出します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.19,0:14:39.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,何でしょう? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.70,0:14:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,23節をご覧ください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.40,0:14:46.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,“兄弟が自分に対して\N何か反感を抱いていることを—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.50,0:14:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“そこで思い出したなら”……\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.04,0:14:54.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,“兄弟は何か反感を抱いているに\N違いない”とあなたは考えます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.98,0:14:58.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,“この前会った時 自分には\N全くあいさつをしてくれなかった”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.98,0:15:01.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,“怒っていたけど\N何があったんだろう？”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.95,0:15:03.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,“全く身に覚えはないけれど—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.75,0:15:05.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,“敏感すぎるんだよ！”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.19,0:15:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“いつも何か 気にいらない\Nことがあるみたいだ”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.46,0:15:15.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスはそういうことを念頭に置いて\N23節を語られたのでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.40,0:15:16.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいえ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.83,0:15:21.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスはその“何か”がどういう事か\N詳細を述べられませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.60,0:15:24.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,どちらが正しいかも述べていません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.91,0:15:27.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,その人が繊細で いつも怒りっぽく—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.58,0:15:33.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,納得せず 人とうまくやっていけない人だ\Nということについて何も述べていません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.45,0:15:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜですか? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.48,0:15:39.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは何が原因だったかということは\N重要ではないからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.56,0:15:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,重要なのは何ですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.09,0:15:46.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和が損なわれていることです！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.26,0:15:49.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,解決すべき不和がそこにあったのです \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.63,0:15:54.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟間の平和の欠如は\Nエホバとの関係に影響します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.60,0:15:57.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとの関係こそ重要です！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.31,0:15:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,では何をすべきですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.14,0:16:02.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,24節に答えがあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.68,0:16:05.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなたの供え物をそこ \N祭壇の前に残しておいて—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.75,0:16:07.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,“出かけてゆきなさい”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.28,0:16:09.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,“まず自分の兄弟と和睦し—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.25,0:16:13.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それから戻って来たときに\Nあなたの供え物をささげなさい”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.52,0:16:17.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,その動物の犠牲も重要です\Nそれは間違いありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.83,0:16:20.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはエホバへの崇拝を表わしており—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.53,0:16:25.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,集会の出席や野外奉仕\Nまた家族の崇拝などが含まれます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.87,0:16:29.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかしイエスによれば\Nもっと重要なものは何ですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.17,0:16:36.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは不和を解決すること　\Nまず兄弟たちとの平和を作ることです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.45,0:16:39.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうするならエホバの崇拝の供え物を—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.11,0:16:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ささげるのにふさわしい\N立場に立てるのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.29,0:16:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,不和を解決することは\Nエホバの恵みをもたらします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.56,0:16:52.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも マタイ5章の原則を\Nいつ適用できますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.86,0:16:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,解決すべき不和があるならいつでもです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.27,0:16:59.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の言動が誤解されるかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.57,0:17:02.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,誤解ではなく 兄弟が傷つくような—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.10,0:17:05.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,明確な理由をこちらが\N作ったのかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.44,0:17:09.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,いずれにしても兄弟が\N傷ついたことに気付きます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.05,0:17:13.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,その場合 平和な関係を作ります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.42,0:17:17.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,また自分が傷つけられたり\N兄弟に対して反感を抱いている場合も—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.82,0:17:20.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,この聖句の原則を適用します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.69,0:17:24.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,率先して行動し 誤解を解き\N不和を解決し— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.76,0:17:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちとの平和を作ることができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.73,0:17:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,この場合も エホバはそうした精神を\N祝福されます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.34,0:17:38.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,では次に マタイ18章を\N開いてみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.24,0:17:42.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,初めに述べたようにこの聖句の適用は\Nさらに限定的なものです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.75,0:17:44.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのようにですか? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.31,0:17:46.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,15節をご覧ください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.65,0:17:49.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,“さらにもしあなたの兄弟が罪を犯したなら—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.65,0:17:54.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,“行ってただあなたと彼との間で\Nその過ちを明らかにしなさい”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.09,0:17:58.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,“彼があなたの述べることを聴くなら\Nあなたは自分の兄弟を得たのです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.66,0:18:03.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここでイエスは “あなたの兄弟が\N罪を犯したなら”と言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.27,0:18:07.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは “何か反感を”いだくこととは\N大きな違いです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.17,0:18:11.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,これはもっと重大な状況について\N述べているのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.01,0:18:12.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな状況ですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.81,0:18:17.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,改訂版の「エホバのご意志を行なう」\Nの136, 7ページによると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.55,0:18:23.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは“借りたお金を返さない場合や\N詐欺を働いた場合など金銭や財産の—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.42,0:18:26.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,“関係した問題であると思われます”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.02,0:18:29.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,“その過ちには中傷が含まれるかもしれません”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.79,0:18:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“人の評判をひどく傷つけたような場合です”\Nとあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.00,0:18:39.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん関係者同士で解決できる罪も\Nありますが もし解決できなければ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.30,0:18:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆から追放されるほど\N由々しい罪もあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.51,0:18:47.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,マタイ 18章15節を適用する前に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.44,0:18:52.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,その段階を本当にとる必要があるか\Nどうかをまず考慮すべきです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.61,0:18:55.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,その人がしたことや\N経済的に被った損失で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.95,0:18:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その人をただ許すことは\Nできないでしょうか? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.22,0:19:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは個人が決めることです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.86,0:19:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,物事を進めるのであれば\Nどのようにしますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.46,0:19:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは15節で ただ二人の間で\N過ちを明らかにしなさいと述べています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.84,0:19:18.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,だれかとその件を話し合って—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.07,0:19:21.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の味方につけよう\Nとしてはなりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.51,0:19:26.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,直接 長老の所に行って二人の問題を\N解決してもらおうとしてはなりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.98,0:19:29.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうではなく二人で解決すべきなのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.99,0:19:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,目標は不和を解決して\Nエホバとの関係を保ち—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.29,0:19:38.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟も同様にするよう\N助けることですから—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.63,0:19:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,初めの努力が成功しなくても\N繰り返し話し合う努力を払います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.43,0:19:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは “誤りを明らかにするために\N一度だけ行きなさい”とは言われませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.91,0:19:55.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,この最初の段階を進めるとき—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.21,0:19:59.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,その動機が“兄弟を得る”ため\Nであることを忘れないでください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.51,0:20:02.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,また 自分はマタイ 18章15節でイエスが述べた—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.92,0:20:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初の段階を適用しようとしていることを\Nはっきりと述べることは助けになるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.72,0:20:13.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん親切に 脅すような仕方ではなく\Nこの問題を解決することが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.46,0:20:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,重大な事であることを示すような\N仕方で伝えます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.87,0:20:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟を得る最初の段階が\Nうまく行かなかったならどうしますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.24,0:20:28.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,16節の第2段階に注目してください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.71,0:20:30.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,“しかし もし彼が聴かないなら—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.88,0:20:34.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなたと一緒にあと一人か二人を\N連れて行きなさい”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.45,0:20:39.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,“一切のことが二人または三人の証人の\N口によって確証されるためです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.86,0:20:43.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうです 一人か二人を伴って\N話すのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.59,0:20:46.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの親友を連れて行くのですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.19,0:20:49.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいえ　\N目的は “兄弟を得る”ことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.80,0:20:54.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,二人の友人とチームになるなら\N兄弟を孤立させてしまいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.94,0:20:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,代わりに他の円熟した\Nクリスチャンを伴うなら受け入れやすいでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.48,0:21:03.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らはどのように\N助けになるでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.51,0:21:06.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,物事を誤解しているでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.52,0:21:09.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,正しく推論するよう\N助けになれますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.95,0:21:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,解決策を見出せますか?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.99,0:21:18.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,霊的に円熟した証人がそこにいれば\N問題を解決する助けになるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.96,0:21:22.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,大抵は 第一か第二の段階で\N兄弟を得て—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.66,0:21:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆の平和が保たれる\N結果となることでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.10,0:21:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,助けようとする繰り返しの努力に\N答え応じない場合はどうなりますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.11,0:21:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたが決定します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.28,0:21:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,経済的な損失が生じてもそれを受け入れ\Nあなたの兄弟を進んで許しますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.35,0:21:46.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,もしさらに事を進めるのであれば—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.92,0:21:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,17節のイエスの言葉に\N耳を傾けてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.66,0:21:56.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,“もし彼がそれらの人たちの述べることを\N聴かないなら会衆に話しなさい”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.67,0:22:00.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,“もし会衆の告げることにさえ\N聴かないならその人を—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.07,0:22:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなたにとって諸国民の者\Nまた収税人のような者としなさい”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.44,0:22:11.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,この段階で会衆を代表している\N長老たちがかかわってきます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.71,0:22:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,長老たちは問題の事実を見直し\N審理委員会を設ける必要があるかを決定します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.49,0:22:21.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,幸いにもこうした状況はまれで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.12,0:22:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,問題は重大な段階に行く前に平和裏に\N解決されることが少なくありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.93,0:22:31.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あの心からのエホバへの祈りに\Nもう一度戻ってみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.50,0:22:36.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは心からの願いを\N聞いてくださるでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.04,0:22:38.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,許してくださいますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.57,0:22:44.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,ところで今 解決しなければならない\N兄弟との不和があることに気付いているなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.28,0:22:47.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,その点についてエホバに祈ってください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.85,0:22:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,感情を克服して 平和を作れるよう\Nエホバの助けを求めてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.16,0:22:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,決して後回しにしないでください！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.49,0:23:02.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスが述べた簡潔な方法に従って\N他の人を許すなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.46,0:23:05.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,条件は整っていることになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.73,0:23:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは犠牲を払ったのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.27,0:23:11.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,ではエホバは何をなさいますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.17,0:23:15.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは”父も許してくださる”\Nと述べました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.18,0:23:18.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,その結果 エホバの恵みと\N祝福を得ることから来る—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.88,0:23:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,清い良心を伴う思いの平安を\N得ることができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.75,0:23:26.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのようにして\Nわたしたちがその一部となっている—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.92,0:23:31.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,美しい一致した兄弟関係に\N大いに貢献することができるのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.43,0:23:37.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,マタイ18章には—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.07,0:23:42.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちと平和や一致を保つ方法\Nに関する教訓がほかにもあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.90,0:23:45.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,不和を解決するのが\N重要であるのと同様—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.81,0:23:50.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは人をつまずかせないように\N注意しなさいと言われました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.41,0:23:53.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベテルの朝の崇拝で\Nスティーブン・レット兄弟は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.42,0:23:57.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,人をつまずかせないための\N3つの方法を説明しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.06,0:24:07.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,“つまずく”というこの絵画的表現は\N思いに鮮明に描くことができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.23,0:24:10.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆 だれかがつまずくのを\N見たことがあり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.07,0:24:13.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分自身つまずくこともあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.10,0:24:16.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その結果の程度は様々です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.00,0:24:19.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,たとえば つまずいても\Nすぐにバランスを取り戻し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.91,0:24:23.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,何事もなく歩き続けることがあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.65,0:24:27.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,また つまずいて倒れ 骨を折り—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.72,0:24:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,大掛かりな治療をして\Nようやく回復する場合もあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.59,0:24:37.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,あるいは つまずいて\N倒れ 頭を打ち—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.86,0:24:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,二度と回復せずに\N犠牲者となるかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.20,0:24:45.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,霊的につまずく場合も同様です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.03,0:24:47.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,すぐに回復する場合もあれば—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.57,0:24:50.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,回復まで時間がかかる場合—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.11,0:24:56.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,あるいは二度と回復せずに\N霊的な犠牲者となる場合もあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.68,0:25:02.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,だれかがつまずくと最終的に\Nどんな結果になるかは分かりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.35,0:25:04.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 注意深くあって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.19,0:25:10.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,決してつまずきの原因とならないように\Nとの警告が与えられているのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.13,0:25:12.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,マタイ 18章を開きましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.73,0:25:16.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,この点で特に力強い聖句があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.33,0:25:20.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,マタイ 18章6節でイエスは\Nこう述べておられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.90,0:25:22.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,“しかし わたしに信仰を置く—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.77,0:25:27.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,“これら小さな者の一人を\Nつまずかせるのがだれであっても—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.34,0:25:32.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,“その者にとっては ろばの回す\Nような臼石を首にかけられて—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.51,0:25:36.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,“広い大海に沈められるほうが\N益になります”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.99,0:25:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,, イエスは写実的な言葉を使い\Nだれかを霊的な犠牲者にするなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.29,0:25:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,永遠の滅びを自分自身にもたらす\Nと述べておられるのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.33,0:25:52.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもここで質問が生じます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.20,0:25:55.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのようにつまずかせて\Nしまうのでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.94,0:25:57.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,興味深いことに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.31,0:26:00.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,だれかを物理的に\Nつまずかせることと—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.08,0:26:04.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,霊的につまずかせることには\N共通点があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.61,0:26:06.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,3つの点を考えましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.78,0:26:12.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,一つ目に だれかを押すことは\Nつまずきの原因となります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.59,0:26:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,特にでこぼこ道ではそう言えます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.12,0:26:20.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは物理的にも霊的にも真実です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.56,0:26:23.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバについて考えてみてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.47,0:26:28.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,だれかを押して ご自身に仕えるよう\N強制することもおできになりますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.64,0:26:32.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,決して力をそのように\Nお用いになりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.41,0:26:39.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,代わりに 招待し 励まし\N決定の結果の祝福や呪いを説明されます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.11,0:26:41.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでも 決定は\N各自にかかっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.88,0:26:46.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,たとえば イザヤ 48章18節で\Nこう述べておられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.66,0:26:51.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ああ あなたがわたしのおきてに\N実際に注意を払いさえすれば！”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.99,0:26:55.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,“そうすれば あなたの平安は\N川のように—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.10,0:26:58.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなたの義は\N海の波のようになるであろうに”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.50,0:27:01.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,強制せずに 訴えておられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.67,0:27:02.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうであれば—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.74,0:27:06.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちが強制することも\N望まれないのではないでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.98,0:27:09.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,たとえば 親は子どもを押して—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.48,0:27:13.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに仕えさせることが\Nないよう注意すべきです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.75,0:27:18.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,かえって エホバのように\N愛情深く心に訴え—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.82,0:27:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな祝福があるかを\Nはっきり示しましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.46,0:27:31.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,別の例として 長老はエホバの羊を\N決して押してはなりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.13,0:27:34.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある長老は自分の割り当ての中で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.47,0:27:38.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,翌朝奉仕に出る人に\N手を挙げてもらいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.81,0:27:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,少ししか手が挙がらないのを見ると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.01,0:27:50.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,もっと出るべきだと会衆を叱りつけ\N浅はかにも再び挙手を求めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.52,0:27:54.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,お察しのとおり 二回目は\Nさらに減りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.52,0:27:59.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかの例として \N聖書研究の司会者は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.89,0:28:04.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,正しいことを行なうよう\N研究生を押すべきではありません \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.60,0:28:07.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,“たばこをやめなさい！\N偶像を処分しなさい！”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.57,0:28:09.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのような圧力ではなく—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.50,0:28:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,心に動機づけを与えれば\N研究生は行動します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.21,0:28:21.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに別の例として\N学校の友達 同僚 親族を押して—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.45,0:28:24.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,真理を受け入れさせようと\Nすべきではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.99,0:28:29.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,押して圧力をかける方法は\Nたとえ誠実さゆえであっても—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.99,0:28:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々をつまずかせ\N何年もの間真理から遠ざけてしまいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.06,0:28:38.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,このことは ある人が\N真理を学び始めたら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.60,0:28:41.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,問題を起こさないよう\N6か月間閉じ込めておくべき—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.90,0:28:44.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,という言葉を思い起こさせます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.61,0:28:47.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし それはまったくの誤りです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.01,0:28:49.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,その熱意ある兄弟を\N閉じ込めるのではなく—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.78,0:28:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,むしろ 見倣うべきです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.41,0:28:58.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,その兄弟が興奮のあまり\N親族や他の人に真理を強制しないよう—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.79,0:29:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,熱意を正しい方向に向ける\N助けがおそらく必要でしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.33,0:29:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 二番目のつまずきの\N原因は何でしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.40,0:29:17.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,道に障害物を置くことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.47,0:29:20.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,物理的にも霊的にもそう言えます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.21,0:29:23.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,意図的であろうと\N無意識であろうと—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.65,0:29:27.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,つまずきのもとを置くなら\N結果は同じです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.62,0:29:31.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日の「ものみの塔」誌の\N注解に述べられているように—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.52,0:29:36.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,健全な話し方をし\N廉直に行動するなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.39,0:29:40.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,決してつまずきのもとを\N置かないよう守られます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.93,0:29:45.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,対照的に 不健全な話し方や\N汚れた行ないは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.77,0:29:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆内外の人をつまずかせます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.54,0:29:54.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,では あることを行なう聖書的な\N権利がある場合はどうでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.08,0:29:58.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,その権利を行使して\Nだれかがつまずいても—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.28,0:30:02.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,言い開きを求められるはずはない\Nと言えるでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.48,0:30:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,コリント第一 8章を開きましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.32,0:30:09.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここにとても興味深い答えがあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.96,0:30:14.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,コリント第一 8章9節\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.80,0:30:19.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,“しかし あなた方のこの権限が\N弱い人たちを何かのことで—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.57,0:30:24.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,“つまずかせるものとならないよう\Nいつも見守っていなさい” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.37,0:30:26.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,興味深いと思いませんか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.57,0:30:29.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,この聖句によれば\N選ぶ権利があっても—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.71,0:30:35.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,だれかをつまずかせる可能性があるなら\Nその権利を行使しないのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.68,0:30:40.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,使徒パウロは同じ章の13節で\N兄弟をつまずかせるなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.62,0:30:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,もはや二度と肉を食べない\Nと述べています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.13,0:30:48.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは ひげを生やすこと—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.10,0:30:53.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,厚化粧をすること \Nアルコールを用いることなど— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.43,0:30:57.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,もしだれかをつまずかせかねないなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.44,0:31:02.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロと同じように喜んで\Nその権利を放棄するでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.71,0:31:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,次に つまずかせる三番目の\N原因は何でしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.68,0:31:10.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,危険について警告しないことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.95,0:31:13.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは手落ちの罪と言えます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.22,0:31:17.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,これも 物理的 霊的に当てはまります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.59,0:31:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,物理的な例として 床にモップが\Nかけられたのを見たとしましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.23,0:31:26.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある人が知らずに濡れた部分に\N近づいてきます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.80,0:31:28.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,警告するでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.94,0:31:33.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,もし警告せずに その人が\N倒れて怪我をすれば—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.71,0:31:37.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちも幾らか責任を\N負うのではないでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.68,0:31:43.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,同様に 霊的にだれかがそれと知らずに\N“誤った歩み”をするとき—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.15,0:31:48.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,ガラテア 6章1節は何をするようにと\N述べているでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.42,0:31:53.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのような人に“再調整を\N施すことに努め”—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.06,0:31:56.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかも“温和な霊をもって”\Nそうします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.60,0:32:00.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,押すのではなく\N優しく 愛情深く警告し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.57,0:32:04.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,再調整を施すことに努めるのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.77,0:32:07.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,決してつまずきの原因とならないよう—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.38,0:32:11.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,注意深くあるべき\N三つの分野を考慮しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.71,0:32:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに仕えるよう\N他の人を押さないこと\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.95,0:32:21.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,たとえ無意識であったとしても\N個人の権利を主張するなどして—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.32,0:32:26.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,つまずきのもとを置くことが\N決してないようにすること\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.39,0:32:33.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,三つ目に 危険に近づく人がいるなら\N愛情深く警告することです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.64,0:32:37.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは\Nつまずきの原因ではなく—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.01,0:32:41.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,良いことを行なう力になりたいと\N思うのではないでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.64,0:32:43.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,堅く立つよう助け—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.58,0:32:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,倒れた人が起き上がるよう\N助けるのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.78,0:32:51.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,だれも兄弟たちを\Nつまずかせたくありませんが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.82,0:32:54.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,注意しないとそうなり得ます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.62,0:32:59.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,人をつまずかせないための\N3つの方法を思い起こしましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.63,0:33:05.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして親 長老 聖書の教え手 \Nまた会衆の仲間の崇拝者として—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.73,0:33:09.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分はどう行動しているかを\N吟味することができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.80,0:33:13.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,一致のために払う努力は\Nいつでも価値があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.47,0:33:19.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹たちと一緒に働いた年月の\N喜ばしい思い出だけを残したいものです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.68,0:33:23.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,73年間の特別全時間\N奉仕を振り返って—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.25,0:33:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エスター・ロサーノ姉妹は\N同様に感じています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.36,0:33:35.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんな “ハニー”って呼ぶけれど\N名前はエスター・ロサーノです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.20,0:33:40.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,1919年に カリフォルニアの\Nフレズノで生まれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.80,0:33:44.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,1935年にバプテスマを受けてから—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.21,0:33:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバへの奉仕を\N本当に楽しんできました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.14,0:33:55.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 特別開拓者になり\Nそれからギレアデに招待されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.15,0:33:57.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,ギレアデの第4期です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.65,0:34:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,1944年のことでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.76,0:34:04.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,特別開拓奉仕を離れるときには—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.79,0:34:09.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな勉強をするのかさえ\N見当もつきませんでしたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.10,0:34:13.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,ギレアデで受ける教育を\N楽しみにしていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.60,0:34:15.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,卒業するとすぐ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.44,0:34:20.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,エスター・ロペス姉妹と共に\N2年間 ブルックリンベテルで働き—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.48,0:34:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 わたしは\Nメキシコに遣わされました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.31,0:34:30.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,1947年にメキシコに来てから\Nずっとここにいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.35,0:34:34.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう68年以上になります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.79,0:34:40.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,来た当時 ベテル奉仕者は7人\N宣教者が22人でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.83,0:34:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,宣教者も支部で一緒に暮らしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.77,0:34:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,メキシコでの業の進展は\N家族の一致と関係しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.34,0:34:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,夫と妻が真理を学べば\N家族みんなも学びます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.48,0:35:01.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,1961年に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.28,0:35:04.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,エスター・ロサーノ姉妹が\N祖父母に証言してくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.45,0:35:09.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,祖父は ”失楽園から復楽園まで”の\N本を通して関心を持ちました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.16,0:35:13.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,奥さんは 本を受け取ると\Nご主人に渡しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.23,0:35:17.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,これこそ自分が探していたものだ\Nと確信した彼は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.17,0:35:21.74,Default2,,0,0,0,, “いつバプテスマを受けられますか？”\Nって言ったんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.74,0:35:25.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,3回の訪問の後\N家族全員が研究に加わりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.17,0:35:29.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,一番上の息子さんは\Nまだ13歳でしたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.54,0:35:33.58,Default2,,0,0,0,, “僕もバプテスマを受ける！”\Nと言いました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.58,0:35:37.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,1年ほど前に\N彼が手紙を持って来てくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.92,0:35:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 自分の家に証言に来てくれて\N本当に嬉しかったと言ってくれたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.43,0:35:49.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしの人生における\N幸福な経験です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.20,0:35:53.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,今では 家族の23人が 四世代に\Nわたってエホバの証人です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.60,0:35:57.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは兄と一緒に \N中央アメリカ支部で奉仕しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.67,0:36:02.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,主人のことを忘れていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.34,0:36:05.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼は 支部の監督でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.18,0:36:07.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じ支部で5年ほど働いていたので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.75,0:36:10.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,お互いのことをよく知っていましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.42,0:36:14.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,奉仕が忙しくて\Nあまり気にしていませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.92,0:36:19.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,結婚が 彼の人生の目標でない\Nことは知っていたので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.09,0:36:23.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,結婚しようと決意したなんて\N気づきませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.93,0:36:26.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,ノア兄弟に手紙を書いて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.30,0:36:30.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしたちが結婚すると聞いたら\N驚きますか”と尋ねました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.94,0:36:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうしたら 兄弟は返事をくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.08,0:36:36.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,手紙の中でノア兄弟は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.41,0:36:39.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,“陽気で話し好きな あなたと—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.15,0:36:43.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,“とても物静かな ロサーノ兄弟“\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.12,0:36:46.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,“非常に興味深い\N組み合わせですね”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.25,0:36:48.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,“お二人が一緒なら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.22,0:36:51.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,真の崇拝において互いに\N助け合っていけるでしょう”—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.83,0:36:54.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,と言ってくださいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.23,0:37:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟からの手紙は\N一番大切な宝物の一つです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.34,0:37:07.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,ルディーが亡くなったとき\Nそのことで くよくよしませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.91,0:37:12.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分はエホバに献身していること\Nそして それを第一にするよう—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.45,0:37:16.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,神が望んでおられることを\N思い起こしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.78,0:37:21.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,神権的な活動に\N一層打ち込むようにしたので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.49,0:37:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,主人の死を過度に\N悲しむことはありませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.03,0:37:32.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,今は 通信部門にいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.97,0:37:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 働くのは\N午前と午後の1時間半ずつで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.44,0:37:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それ以外の時間は部屋で研究しています\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.98,0:37:48.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,まだ 朝の崇拝に出席し—\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.22,0:37:53.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,奉仕にも参加できることを\N嬉しく思っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.96,0:37:57.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,毎週 二件の研究を司会しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.23,0:38:07.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに自分の命を捧げた人たちと\N共にいられるのは喜びです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.57,0:38:09.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが 彼らを—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.20,0:38:14.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご自分の大切な息子や娘たち\Nとみなしておられるので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.04,0:38:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしも幸せです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.21,0:38:23.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,どういう訳か\N宣教者の多くが訪ねてきてくれて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.05,0:38:26.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしが励みになってきたと\N言ってくれます \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.39,0:38:29.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも彼らこそ\Nわたしの励みです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.92,0:38:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,長年にわたり 見倣うべき\N素晴らしい手本に囲まれてきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.76,0:38:39.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,神にお仕えできる\N素晴らしい特権について—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.93,0:38:41.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしはただ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.87,0:38:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,, エホバに感謝しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.68,0:38:55.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロサーノ姉妹は\N割り当てに留まり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.18,0:39:00.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々と親しい友情の絆を結ぶ点で\N素晴らしい模範です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.45,0:39:03.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,姉妹が得たほかの祝福にも\N気付かれましたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.79,0:39:08.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは全時間奉仕の目標を共にした\N配偶者を見いだしたことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.80,0:39:12.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,すべての交際が結婚に\N至るわけではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.57,0:39:15.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,交際中でお互いに\N気持ちがあるとしても—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.37,0:39:18.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは配偶者となる人との\N違いや欠点を—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.37,0:39:21.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,正直に見ることができますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.31,0:39:23.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを受け入れますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.18,0:39:27.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,それとも関係を終わらせるほど\N重大な問題でしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.65,0:39:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“結婚に備える”シリーズの3番目の\N最後のビデオではこの状況が描かれます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.33,0:39:41.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,ついに大切な日が来ました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.80,0:39:45.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,数か月準備し 想像した通りです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.80,0:39:48.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,あっ 待って!—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.50,0:39:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼女じゃなくて...\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.01,0:39:53.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,こっちがわたしです \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.91,0:40:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その日 妹が結婚するのを見て—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.49,0:40:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の将来を考えさせられました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.57,0:40:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,シェーンと付き合い始めた時—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.94,0:40:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,すべてがうまくいっていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.83,0:40:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,何時間も電話で話しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.55,0:41:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,お互いにひかれ合っていたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.07,0:41:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼だと確信していました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.52,0:41:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 徐々に気になることが\N出てきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.20,0:42:03.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼の傾向が見え始めたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.73,0:42:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,改善していくとも思えませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.12,0:43:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,目標が同じかどうかも\N分からなくなりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.17,0:43:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,独りぼっちみたい...\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.98,0:43:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも そうではなかったんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.16,0:43:35.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,母は優しく様子を聞いてくれたので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.06,0:43:37.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,気持ちを話せました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.70,0:43:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“多分 彼ではないと思う...”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.70,0:43:45.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうすべきか言われる\Nと思っていたけれど—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.27,0:43:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,違いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.91,0:43:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“彼でなくてもあなたは大丈夫よ”\Nと言って安心させてくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.24,0:44:22.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,塔を建てる際にイエスが言われたことを\N思い起こさせてくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.88,0:44:27.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,“たとえば あなた方のうちのだれが\N 塔を建てようと思う場合—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.38,0:44:29.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,“まず座って費用を計算し—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.62,0:44:32.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,“自分がそれを完成するだけのものを\N 持っているかどうかを—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.79,0:44:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“調べないでしょうか？”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.29,0:44:37.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは “シェーンとの関係”という—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.42,0:44:40.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,建設プロジェクトを\N始めようとしていたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.73,0:44:45.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,だからそれにとりかかる前に\N“費用を計算する”必要もあるんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.80,0:44:48.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,両親は 心配していることを—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.47,0:44:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,シェーンと話し合うよう\N励ましてくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.04,0:44:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.92,0:45:06.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,母の言ったとおり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.95,0:45:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは大丈夫でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.06,0:45:11.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に大丈夫だったんです \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.69,0:45:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしはシェーンと\N別れることにしました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.17,0:45:20.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,数年後—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.63,0:45:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,, 自分と同じようにエホバを\N愛している兄弟に出会いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.84,0:45:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,心から彼を愛しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.02,0:45:40.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,姉妹は賢明にも自分のことを\N建設プロジェクトと比較しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.32,0:45:44.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,交際期間中に見たすべての特質の\N“費用を計算”しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.99,0:45:48.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,結婚で問題を抱えてしまう\Nずっと前にです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.93,0:45:52.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん配偶者に\N完全さを期待すべきではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.83,0:45:55.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし交際期間中に\N物事に取り組むことは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.74,0:45:57.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和裏に不和を解決するために—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.60,0:46:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが与えてくださった\N一つの機会です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.98,0:46:04.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,成功したクリスチャン同士の結婚には—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.18,0:46:06.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,共通点があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.31,0:46:08.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを第一にし—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.05,0:46:12.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,神に対する互いの献身を\N支持することです \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.69,0:46:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,これはモリッツ夫妻にとっても同様です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.19,0:46:19.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,二人はオーストラレーシア支部で\N奉仕しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.53,0:46:22.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,二人は結婚して65年になり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.03,0:46:26.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,全時間奉仕は合わせて\N131年になります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.53,0:46:29.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの組織内で何を行なうかを\N決定しようとしている—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.60,0:46:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,若者へのアドバイスを聞きましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.04,0:46:40.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは1948年11月に\N開拓奉仕を始めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.78,0:46:42.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,ずいぶん前のことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.75,0:46:45.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,開拓者になると決めたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.35,0:46:49.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでこう言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.09,0:46:52.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,“エホバ あなたの\N 求めていることをします”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.26,0:46:55.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,“どんな割り当ても受け入れ\N どこへでも行きます”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.80,0:46:59.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,“割り当ては求めませんが\N 断わることはしません”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.47,0:47:02.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,開拓奉仕以外のことは\N考えていませんでしたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.50,0:47:05.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,1年したとき\N封筒を受け取りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.57,0:47:09.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,手紙には “同封の用紙に\N記入してください”とあり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.71,0:47:11.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベテルの申込書でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.61,0:47:14.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,“まさか ベテルとは！”と\N 思いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.38,0:47:16.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバにはどこへでも行くと\N述べたので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.55,0:47:19.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,とにかくやろうと思いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.59,0:47:21.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしはプリンタリーで奉仕し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.69,0:47:25.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,インキの缶を洗ったり\N印刷予定を作ったりしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.73,0:47:28.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,そしてプレスでも働きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.56,0:47:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも ほどなくして\N事務所に割り当てられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.94,0:47:37.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベテルでは多くのことを学べます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.70,0:47:40.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちと\Nうまく生活する方法や—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.34,0:47:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの組織がどのように機能するかを\N学ぶこともできます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.01,0:47:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは経験豊かな兄弟たちと\N一緒に奉仕する特権がありました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.55,0:47:54.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしはメトロポリタン会衆に\N割り当てられ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.52,0:47:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこにアンがいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.29,0:48:01.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは\N1951年10月に結婚し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.63,0:48:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,2週間後に わたしは\N開拓奉仕を始めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.07,0:48:09.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,巡回奉仕を始めた時\Nわたしは20歳でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.87,0:48:13.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは1年しか開拓奉仕を\Nしていませんでしたから—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.74,0:48:16.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,油そそがれた者たちも含む—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.11,0:48:19.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,長年の開拓者の姉妹たちと\N証言することに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.71,0:48:22.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,不安を抱いていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.65,0:48:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,半分泣きながら\Nメルボルンに行きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.39,0:48:31.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹たち 特に子どもたちと\N親しくなれたのは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.16,0:48:33.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても楽しかったです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.36,0:48:37.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 1958年に\Nニューヨークでの国際大会に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.36,0:48:40.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,出席する機会がありました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.27,0:48:44.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちが出席することを\N知った協会は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.24,0:48:47.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,ギレアデの申込書を送ってきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.07,0:48:50.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,“どうしよう? \N やっていけるだろうか？”と思いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.91,0:48:54.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも “いやとは言わない”ことに\Nしていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.08,0:48:59.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,大会の後 わたしたちは\Nカナダに6か月間—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.69,0:49:02.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,特別開拓者として割り当てられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.66,0:49:06.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,ノア兄弟はわたしたち\N英連邦諸国からの40人を—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.86,0:49:09.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,冷凍庫で保存すると言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.56,0:49:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは楽しい経験でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.00,0:49:16.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,初めて冬を経験しましたが\Nとにかくやりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.40,0:49:20.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,雪や氷や つららの写真を撮って—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.17,0:49:23.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,インドやアフリカの割り当ての際に\N見せようと思っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.98,0:49:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバのユーモアで\Nフィンランドに割り当てられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.62,0:49:32.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,ギレアデや他の学校の授業は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.02,0:49:33.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの組織—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.52,0:49:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,およびそれがどのように機能するかを\N理解する助けとなります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.23,0:49:44.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,フィンランドについては\Nあまり知りませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.13,0:49:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,寒くて きれいで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.00,0:49:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,オーストラリアからは\N遠いことくらいでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.41,0:49:55.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,オーストラリアからは\N遠く離れているので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.88,0:49:57.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族に会うために\N家に帰ることが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.84,0:50:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,しばらくはできなくなることを\N知っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.75,0:50:06.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,フィンランドに移動したとき—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.99,0:50:09.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロシアの兄弟たちは禁令下にいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.12,0:50:12.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,必要とされていた霊的な食物を—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.13,0:50:15.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,供給しなければなりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.63,0:50:17.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで旅行者を送り込み—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.56,0:50:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,地元の兄弟たちに会って\N食物を供給しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.37,0:50:26.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの祝福と聖霊がなければ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.97,0:50:29.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,何一つ行なえませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.54,0:50:31.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,供給された霊的食物の—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.28,0:50:34.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,量の多さには驚かされます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.21,0:50:37.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それらが翻訳され提供されたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.02,0:50:40.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうした事が何の事故もなく—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.05,0:50:42.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,20年以上続けられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.46,0:50:45.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの祝福なしではありえません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.73,0:50:49.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,フィンランドを去るのは\N簡単ではありませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.36,0:50:51.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,複雑な気持ちでしたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.20,0:50:53.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際には割り当ての上に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.07,0:50:55.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバのみ手を感じました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.30,0:50:58.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは両親が助けを\N必要としていた時に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.27,0:51:00.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,オーストラリアに戻ったからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.67,0:51:03.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベテルや全時間奉仕を離れることなく—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.48,0:51:05.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,援助することができたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.91,0:51:09.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,1999年にロシアに行くように言われ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.02,0:51:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,2年半ほどいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.12,0:51:14.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロシアに行くことは少し不安でしたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.96,0:51:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,これまでに経験した\N最も思い出に残る割り当てでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.49,0:51:23.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロシアではずっと禁令でしたから—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.10,0:51:26.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちは家から家の奉仕には\N慣れていませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.60,0:51:29.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,戸口ですぐ会話を始めないので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.27,0:51:32.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,家の人は何の用で来たのか\N知りたがります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.84,0:51:36.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,通りで会った人を\N再訪問することができません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.78,0:51:39.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,どこに住んでいるかわからないからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.55,0:51:43.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも家を訪問するなら\N再訪問はできます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.72,0:51:46.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちはその利点に気づきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.69,0:51:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは学ぶべき新たな事柄でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.09,0:51:54.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,巡回監督は会衆の訪問の仕方を\N学ぶ必要がありました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.69,0:51:58.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,ポーランドの兄弟たちが\N巡回訪問の援助をしましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.33,0:52:01.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らも学はなければなりませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.54,0:52:03.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,長年の禁令下での奉仕から—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.87,0:52:07.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,いまや世界の他の場所と\N同じ方法で奉仕することは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.54,0:52:09.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,実に大きな変化でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.68,0:52:13.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしが下した最善の決定は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.35,0:52:15.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,命をエホバのみ手にゆだね—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.82,0:52:19.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,“行くべき道と\N すべきことを決めてください”と—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.12,0:52:21.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに述べたことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.29,0:52:23.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,今も同じ気持ちでいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.82,0:52:25.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分のしたことすべては—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.83,0:52:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,何らかの訓練になってきたと\N思っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.06,0:52:33.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,今していることも\N新しい世のための訓練です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.13,0:52:35.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分にあまり時間がないからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.87,0:52:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな割り当てでしょうか？\N楽しみです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.07,0:52:44.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,お勧めしたいのは\N自分で決めないことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.58,0:52:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに決めてもらうのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.12,0:52:53.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,モリッツ兄弟姉妹は割り当てに関して—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.19,0:52:55.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,常にエホバを見ていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.66,0:52:57.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,モリッツ兄弟にとって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.16,0:53:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはフィンランド, インド, \Nロシア, ポーランド, ウクライナ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.00,0:53:05.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,またオーストラレーシアで\N支部委員として奉仕し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.30,0:53:10.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,また 本部代表として70以上の国を\N訪問する特権を意味したのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.84,0:53:12.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,確かに状況が許すなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.87,0:53:16.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのような形の奉仕でも\N追い求めることができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.74,0:53:18.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,導きを祈り求める際—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.75,0:53:21.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちはエホバの組織と\N自分にとって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.18,0:53:23.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,最善の益となるところに\N遣わしてくだるよう—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.98,0:53:25.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに物事をゆだねます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.65,0:53:30.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,野外での新たな割り当てを受けた\Nベテル奉仕者たちは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.96,0:53:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバのご意志を喜んで\N行なう精神を示しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.40,0:53:40.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベテルでの仕事の調整は\N宣べ伝える業の重要性を示しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.57,0:53:42.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,経験ある聖書の教え手を含む—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.74,0:53:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに多くの資産が忙しい収穫の業に\N振り向けられています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.44,0:53:50.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,南アフリカ支部からの報告では—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.81,0:53:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,神権的な指示に従う忠節な人々の声を\N聞くことができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.92,0:54:03.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,2015年9月23日\N統治体はすべての支部で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.02,0:54:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベテル家族の規模が縮小される\Nという発表を行ないました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.63,0:54:15.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分としては9月23日水曜日の\Nその発表はわくわくさせるものでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.14,0:54:17.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても重要な発表だと分かりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.77,0:54:21.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,その発表で終わりが\Nいかに近づいているかが分かり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.51,0:54:23.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,目に涙があふれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.28,0:54:27.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,目をつむり “なんでも行ないます”と\Nエホバに言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.38,0:54:32.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,割り当て変更の知らせを受け取った\N当初は ぼう然としていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.62,0:54:38.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,割り当て変更の知らせを受けた時\Nはじめはとても不安な気持ちでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.99,0:54:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは自分にはあまり\N関係ないと思っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.23,0:54:47.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,かなりショックでしたし\N悲しくなりましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.03,0:54:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベテルや会衆の兄弟たちに\N励まされました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.84,0:54:54.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体の指示は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.37,0:54:58.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちが正規開拓者としての\N割り当てを受けることでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.68,0:55:02.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,木曜日には開拓者の\N申し込み書に記入しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.98,0:55:05.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,サムエル第一 12章22節には—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.99,0:55:07.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,“エホバはその偉大な\Nみ名のために—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.99,0:55:11.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ご自分の民を捨て去ることは\Nされない”とあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.56,0:55:15.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベテルのことは決して忘れません\N素晴らしいものでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.23,0:55:19.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも開拓奉仕に集中して\N楽しみたいと思います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.40,0:55:23.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,特に祈り求めたのは\N宣教に注意を集中するために—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.70,0:55:28.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,できるだけ簡素な生活ができるような\N場所を見いだすということでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.51,0:55:32.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,割り当ての変更を受けた皆さん\Nすべてにお伝えしたいことは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.18,0:55:36.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはわたしたちの父であり\Nその責任を放棄することは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.68,0:55:38.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,決してないということです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.45,0:55:40.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,世話してくださいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.02,0:55:44.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,4組の夫婦が会衆からいなくなります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.29,0:55:48.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,割り当てられた会衆には\N彼らが真の霊的な人で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.19,0:55:51.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,新たな会衆にとって\N貴重な資産になる人々であることを—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.63,0:55:54.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,伝えたいと思います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.97,0:56:00.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆の兄弟たちに\N感謝したいと思います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.71,0:56:06.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,世俗の仕事や ボニーが述べたように\N宿舎も見つけてくれたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.65,0:56:09.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,おかげで割り当てが\Nとても楽しみになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.95,0:56:14.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん これがエホバから\N来ていることを知っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.59,0:56:19.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,支部委員会は“この件はすぐに\N進める必要がある”と言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.43,0:56:23.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは “物事を決めるために\N2-3週間の猶予”を—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.16,0:56:25.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベテル家族に求めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.23,0:56:27.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,諸会衆に電話で連絡が取られ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.47,0:56:31.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベテル家族には仕事や\N宿舎が提供されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.01,0:56:37.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,二人の若いベテル奉仕者が\N来てくれたので会衆は喜びました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.18,0:56:40.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆にはかなりの数の若者がいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.51,0:56:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,若者たちは二人からすでに\Nたくさんの益を受けています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.02,0:56:47.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,二人のために住む場所を\N見つけたり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.45,0:56:53.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆の一員として腰を据えて\N活動したりできるよう援助しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.16,0:56:56.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,わが家へようこそ\N移動して1週間です \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.50,0:57:01.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちが家のペンキ塗り タイル張り\N掃除などを手伝ってくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.87,0:57:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当にたくさんのことを\Nしてくださいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.00,0:57:07.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,これはベテルの思い出です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.37,0:57:10.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,6か月前には開拓者学校を楽しみました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.88,0:57:14.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちのおかげで\N仕事が見つかりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.21,0:57:17.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはずっと祈りに答えてくださり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.05,0:57:22.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,時には祈る前からわたしたちの\N不安に答えてくださいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.22,0:57:25.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,南アフリカにおける\Nこの感動的な経験は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.73,0:57:28.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界中で見られています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.86,0:57:31.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちの示す互いへの愛は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.53,0:57:36.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちに対する\Nエホバの偉大な愛の反映です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.30,0:57:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,このすばらしい兄弟関係を\Nエホバに感謝します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.21,0:57:48.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体は神権的な指示に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.41,0:57:52.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,忠節に答え応じる兄弟たちに\N深く感謝しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.85,0:57:55.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,変化は常に簡単では\Nありませんが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.32,0:57:58.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,新たな霊的備えや\N業の調整の上にある—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.22,0:58:02.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの祝福を見るなら\N助けが得られます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.63,0:58:05.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちからの感謝の手紙によって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.06,0:58:10.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体はエホバが組織を導いておられる\Nとの確信を増し加えています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.40,0:58:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,アメリカの一姉妹はJW Broadcasting\Nについてこう書きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.01,0:58:21.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,“プログラムはよく祈りに対する\N直接の答えのように感じます”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.08,0:58:25.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,特に大変だった一日のあと\Nこう言っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.02,0:58:29.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,“エホバからの贈り物として\N今日家で何を見つけたと思いますか？”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.62,0:58:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“落胆に対処する方法を扱った\N3月のブロードキャスティングです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.83,0:58:39.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,2016年1月のブロード\Nキャスティングを見た後—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.30,0:58:42.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,オーストリアの一家族はこう書きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.44,0:58:46.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,“長男はドイツのゼルターズの\N支部で奉仕しています”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.91,0:58:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“自慢の息子ですが \Nとても寂しく感じています”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.08,0:58:55.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ですから「わたしの宝を」\Nという歌が大好きです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.05,0:59:00.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしたちの気持ちや犠牲を\N理解してくださり うれしくなります”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.79,0:59:05.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは確かに必要とするものを\N必要な時に与えくださいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.43,0:59:08.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかも あらゆる種類のものをです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.93,0:59:10.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えばこのミュージック・ビデオは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.93,0:59:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,不和を解決するという論題に\Nふさわしいものでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.40,0:59:19.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い母親とその姑の状況が\N最初に出てきますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.17,0:59:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“互いに許し合う”ことを\N思い起こさせてくれます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.66,0:59:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは 親切で\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.36,0:59:49.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつもよく気がつくの\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.94,0:59:55.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも心が壊れそう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.54,0:59:59.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,気持ちすれ違い\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.85,1:00:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,涙こぼれる\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.25,1:00:10.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,陽が沈む前に\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.89,1:00:17.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,目と目合わせながら\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.40,1:00:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,心に寄り添えば　見える\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.24,1:00:31.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの 優しさ\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.74,1:00:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,時にはぶつかり合い\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.65,1:00:44.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,君の良さ　見えなくて\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.59,1:00:49.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも信じていたい\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.43,1:00:53.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,僕たちはきっと\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.60,1:00:58.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じ思いさ\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.91,1:01:04.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,陽が沈む前に\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.81,1:01:11.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,友の声 探して\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.02,1:01:18.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,傷ついた心 振り捨て\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.83,1:01:25.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,ふたりの 明日を見る\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.20,1:01:30.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛の絆\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.27,1:01:37.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,簡単には ほどけない\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.94,1:01:44.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,許すたび 強くなる\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.22,1:01:49.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう 振り返らない\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.22,1:01:55.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,陽が沈む前に\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.03,1:02:01.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,目と目合わせながら\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.47,1:02:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,心に寄り添えば 見える\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.54,1:02:16.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,静かに 動き出す\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.99,1:02:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,奏でる 愛のハーモニー\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.17,1:02:41.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,許す必要のある二つの重大な分野に\N気付きましたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.67,1:02:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族と会衆という分野です\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.68,1:02:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,この不完全な世にあっては\Nいつでも許すべき理由があります\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.12,1:02:55.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに見倣い 人を許す機会を\N生活の中で求めてください\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.82,1:03:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,結びに ニューヨーク ウォーウィック\Nにある世界本部を訪問しましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.66,1:03:05.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベテル家族はこの新しい\N仕事場へと移動しています\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.87,1:03:10.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,2万5千人以上の兄弟姉妹たちが\Nこの施設の建設で働きました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.84,1:03:13.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,これはテンポラリー・ボランティア—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.84,1:03:17.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,建設サーバント ベテル奉仕者\N建設グループ そして—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.68,1:03:21.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,これまでの王国会館プロジェクトで\N働いたボランティアの—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.18,1:03:24.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,結集した努力の賜物です\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.45,1:03:25.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,今年の初め—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.62,1:03:30.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界本部の奉仕者の到着に備えて\N最終的な準備が行なわれました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.92,1:03:33.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,見学が始まると 訪問者たちは—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.69,1:03:38.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の歴史的展示物 \N視覚に訴えるエホバの証人の歴史—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.73,1:03:43.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,またエホバが組織を今日どのように\N導いておられるかを説明した—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.04,1:03:46.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,参加型のミュージアムを楽しめます\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.64,1:03:51.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界本部の完成を助けてくださった\N皆さんのことをエホバに感謝します\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.68,1:03:53.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,それには幾千人ものボランティア—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.98,1:03:57.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,また定期的な寄付を通して\N世界的な業を支えてくださった—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.68,1:04:00.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹たちも含まれています\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.99,1:04:02.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんに愛をお送りし—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.69,1:04:07.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが一致した兄弟関係を\N祝福してくださるよう祈ります\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.16,1:04:08.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,ニューヨーク市ブルックリンから\NJW Broadcastingでした!\N
